#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/chapter04/aboutsbus.xml:11
msgid "About SBUs"
msgstr "SBU에 대해"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/aboutsbus.xml:13
msgid ""
"Many people would like to know beforehand approximately how long it takes to "
"compile and install each package. Because Linux From Scratch can be built on "
"many different systems, it is impossible to provide absolute time estimates. "
"The biggest package (gcc) will take approximately 5 minutes on the fastest "
"systems, but could take days on slower systems! Instead of providing actual "
"times, the Standard Build Unit (SBU) measure will be used instead."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/aboutsbus.xml:22
msgid ""
"The SBU measure works as follows. The first package to be compiled is "
"binutils in <xref linkend=\"chapter-cross-tools\"/>. The time it takes to "
"compile using one core is what we will refer to as the Standard Build Unit "
"or SBU. All other compile times will be expressed in terms of this unit of "
"time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/aboutsbus.xml:28
msgid ""
"For example, consider a package whose compilation time is 4.5 SBUs. This "
"means that if your system took 4 minutes to compile and install the first "
"pass of binutils, it will take <emphasis>approximately</emphasis> 18 minutes "
"to build the example package.  Fortunately, most build times are shorter "
"than one SBU."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/aboutsbus.xml:34
msgid ""
"SBUs are not entirely accurate because they depend on many factors, "
"including the host system's version of GCC.  They are provided here to give "
"an estimate of how long it might take to install a package, but the numbers "
"can vary by as much as dozens of minutes in some cases."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/aboutsbus.xml:39
msgid ""
"On some newer systems, the motherboard is capable of controlling the system "
"clock speed. This can be controlled with a command such as "
"<command>powerprofilesctl</command>. This is not available in LFS, but may "
"be available on the host distro. After LFS is complete, it can be added to a "
"system with the procedures at the <ulink url='&blfs-book;sysutils/power-"
"profiles-daemon.html'> BLFS power-profiles-daemon</ulink> page.  Before "
"measuring the build time of any package it is advisable to use a system "
"power profile set for maximum performance (and maximum power consumption).  "
"Otherwise the measured SBU value may be inaccurate because the system may "
"react differently when building <xref linkend='ch-tools-binutils-pass1'/> or "
"other packages.  Be aware that a significant inaccuracy can still show up "
"even if the same profile is used for both packages because the system may "
"respond slower if the system is idle when starting the build procedure. "
"Setting the power profile to <quote>performance</quote> will minimize this "
"problem.  And obviously doing so will also make the system build LFS faster."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/aboutsbus.xml:61
msgid ""
"If <command>powerprofilesctl</command> is available, issue the "
"<command>powerprofilesctl set performance</command> command to select the "
"<literal>performance</literal> profile.  Some distros provides the "
"<command>tuned-adm</command> command for managing the profiles instead of "
"<command>powerprofilesctl</command>, on these distros issue the "
"<command>tuned-adm profile throughput-performance</command> command to "
"select the <literal>throughput-performance</literal> profile."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><note><para>
#: en/chapter04/aboutsbus.xml:70
msgid ""
"When multiple processors are used in this way, the SBU units in the book "
"will vary even more than they normally would.  In some cases, the make step "
"will simply fail.  Analyzing the output of the build process will also be "
"more difficult because the lines from different processes will be "
"interleaved.  If you run into a problem with a build step, revert to a "
"single processor build to properly analyze the error messages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><note><para>
#: en/chapter04/aboutsbus.xml:77
msgid ""
"The times presented here for all packages (except <xref linkend='ch-tools-"
"binutils-pass1'/> which is based on one core)  are based upon using four "
"cores (-j4). The times in Chapter 8 also include the time to run the "
"regression tests for the package unless specified otherwise."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/chapter04/abouttestsuites.xml:11
msgid "About the Test Suites"
msgstr "테스트 스위트에 대해"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/abouttestsuites.xml:13
msgid ""
"Most packages provide a test suite. Running the test suite for a newly built "
"package is a good idea because it can provide a <quote>sanity check</quote> "
"indicating that everything compiled correctly. A test suite that passes its "
"set of checks usually proves that the package is functioning as the "
"developer intended. It does not, however, guarantee that the package is "
"totally bug free."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/abouttestsuites.xml:20
msgid ""
"Some test suites are more important than others. For example, the test "
"suites for the core toolchain packages&mdash;GCC, binutils, and "
"glibc&mdash;are of the utmost importance due to their central role in a "
"properly functioning system. The test suites for GCC and glibc can take a "
"very long time to complete, especially on slower hardware, but are strongly "
"recommended."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><note><para>
#: en/chapter04/abouttestsuites.xml:28
msgid ""
"Running the test suites in <xref linkend=\"chapter-cross-tools\"/> and <xref "
"linkend=\"chapter-temporary-tools\"/> is pointless; since the test programs "
"are compiled with a cross-compiler, they probably can't run on the build "
"host."
msgstr ""
"<xref linkend=\"chapter-cross-tools\"/> 및 <xref linkend=\"chapter-temporary-"
"tools\"/>에서 테스트 스위트를 실행하는 것은 의미 없습니다. 왜? 테스트 프로그"
"램이 교차 컴파일러로 빌드되었기 때문에, 아마도 빌드 호스트에서는 실행할 수 없"
"을 것이기 때문."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/abouttestsuites.xml:34
msgid ""
"A common issue with running the test suites for binutils and GCC is running "
"out of pseudo terminals (PTYs). This can result in a large number of failing "
"tests. This may happen for several reasons, but the most likely cause is "
"that the host system does not have the <systemitem "
"class=\"filesystem\">devpts</systemitem> file system set up correctly. This "
"issue is discussed in greater detail at <ulink url=\"&lfs-root;lfs/"
"faq.html#no-ptys\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/abouttestsuites.xml:42
msgid ""
"Sometimes package test suites will fail for reasons which the developers are "
"aware of and have deemed non-critical. Consult the logs located at <ulink "
"url=\"&test-results;\"/> to verify whether or not these failures are "
"expected. This site is valid for all test suites throughout this book."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/chapter04/addinguser.xml:11
msgid "Adding the LFS User"
msgstr "LFS 사용자 추가"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/addinguser.xml:13
msgid ""
"When logged in as user <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem>, "
"making a single mistake can damage or destroy a system. Therefore, the "
"packages in the next two chapters are built as an unprivileged user.  You "
"could use your own user name, but to make it easier to set up a clean "
"working environment, we will create a new user called <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem> as a member of a new group (also named "
"<systemitem class=\"groupname\">lfs</systemitem>) and run commands as &lfs-"
"user; during the installation process. As <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem>, issue the following commands to add "
"the new user:"
msgstr ""
"<systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> 사용자로 로그인하면 단 한 번"
"의 실수도 시스템을 손상시키거나 깨뜨릴 수 있습니다. 따라서, 다음 두 장에 나오"
"는 패키지는 권한 없는 일반 사용자로 빌드합니다. 자신의 사용자 이름을 사용할 "
"수도 있지만, 깨끗한 작업 환경을 더 쉽게 구축하기 위해 <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem>라는 새 그룹(마찬가지로 이름은 "
"<systemitem class=\"groupname\">lfs</systemitem>)의 구성원인 <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem> 새 사용자를 생성하고, 설치 과정 동안 "
"&lfs-user; 권한으로 명령어를 실행하십시오. <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem> 권한으로 다음 명령어 실행하여 새 사용자 "
"추가:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter04/addinguser.xml:23
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>groupadd &lfs-groupname;\n"
"useradd -s /bin/bash -g &lfs-groupname; -m -k /dev/null &lfs-username;</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><title>
#: en/chapter04/addinguser.xml:27
msgid "This is what the command line options mean:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter04/addinguser.xml:30
msgid "<parameter>-s /bin/bash</parameter>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter04/addinguser.xml:32
msgid ""
"This makes <command>bash</command> the default shell for user <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter04/addinguser.xml:38
msgid "<parameter>-g lfs</parameter>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter04/addinguser.xml:40
msgid ""
"This option adds user <systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem> to "
"group <systemitem class=\"groupname\">lfs</systemitem>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter04/addinguser.xml:46
msgid "<parameter>-m</parameter>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter04/addinguser.xml:48
msgid ""
"This creates a home directory for <systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</"
"systemitem>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter04/addinguser.xml:54
msgid "<parameter>-k /dev/null</parameter>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter04/addinguser.xml:56
msgid ""
"This parameter prevents possible copying of files from a skeleton directory "
"(the default is <filename class=\"directory\">/etc/skel</filename>)  by "
"changing the input location to the special null device."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter04/addinguser.xml:63
msgid "<parameter>lfs</parameter>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter04/addinguser.xml:65
msgid "This is the name of the new user."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/addinguser.xml:71
msgid ""
"If you want to log in as &lfs-user; or switch to &lfs-user; from a non-"
"&root; user (as opposed to switching to user &lfs-user; when logged in as "
"&root;, which does not require the &lfs-user; user to have a password), you "
"need to set a password for &lfs-user;.  Issue the following command as the "
"&root; user to set the password:"
msgstr ""
"만약 &lfs-user; 사용자로 직접 로그인하거나, &root; 아닌 일반 사용자 상태에서 "
"&lfs-user; 사용자로 전환하고 싶다면(이미 &root; 로그인한 상태에서 &lfs-user; "
"전환하는 것과는 대조적이며, 이 경우 &lfs-user; 비밀번호가 필요하지 않습니"
"다), &lfs-user; 위한 비밀번호를 설정해야 합니다. &root; 사용자 권한으로 다음 "
"명령어를 실행하여 비밀번호를 설정:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter04/addinguser.xml:77
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>passwd &lfs-username;</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/addinguser.xml:79
msgid ""
"Grant <systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem> full access to all the "
"directories under <filename class=\"directory\">$LFS</filename> by making "
"<systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem> the owner:"
msgstr ""
"<systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem>를 소유자로 지정하여, "
"<filename class=\"directory\">$LFS</filename> 아래 모든 디렉터리에 대한 전체 "
"권한을 <systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem>에게 부여:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter04/addinguser.xml:83
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>chown -v &lfs-username; $LFS/{usr{,/*},var,etc,tools}\n"
"case $(uname -m) in\n"
"  x86_64) chown -v &lfs-username; $LFS/lib64 ;;\n"
"esac</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><note><para>
#: en/chapter04/addinguser.xml:88
msgid ""
"In some host systems, the following <command>su</command> command does not "
"complete properly and suspends the login for the &lfs-user; user to the "
"background.  If the prompt \"lfs:~$\" does not appear immediately, entering "
"the <command>fg</command> command will fix the issue."
msgstr ""
"일부 호스트 시스템에서는 다음 <command>su</command> 명령어가 제대로 완료되지 "
"않고 &lfs-user; 사용자 로그인을 백그라운드로 일시 중단시킵니다. 만약 \"lfs:~$"
"\" 프롬프트가 즉시 나타나지 않는다면, <command>fg</command> 명령어를 입력하"
"여 문제를 해결할 수 있습니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/addinguser.xml:93
msgid ""
"Next, start a shell running as user &lfs-user;. This can be done by logging "
"in as &lfs-user; on a virtual console, or with the following substitute/"
"switch user command:"
msgstr ""
"다음, &lfs-user; 사용자로 실행되는 셸을 시작합니다. 가상 콘솔에서 &lfs-user; "
"로 로그인하거나, 다음의 사용자 교체/전환 명령어 사용:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter04/addinguser.xml:97
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>su - &lfs-username;</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/addinguser.xml:99
msgid ""
"The <quote><parameter>-</parameter></quote> instructs <command>su</command> "
"to start a login shell as opposed to a non-login shell.  The difference "
"between these two types of shells is described in detail in <ulink "
"role='man' url='&man;bash.1'>bash(1)</ulink> and <command>info bash</"
"command>."
msgstr ""
"<quote><parameter>-</parameter></quote>는 <command>su</command>가 로그인 셸"
"을 시작하도록 지시합니다. 이 두 가지 유형의 셸 간 차이점은 <ulink role='man' "
"url='&man;bash.1'>bash(1)</ulink> 및 <command>info bash</command>에 자세히 설"
"명되어 있습니다."

#. type: Attribute 'xreflabel' of: <chapter>
#: en/chapter04/chapter04.xml:8
msgid "Chapter&nbsp;4"
msgstr "제4장"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><title>
#: en/chapter04/chapter04.xml:12
msgid "Final Preparations"
msgstr "마지막 준비"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/chapter04/creatingminlayout.xml:11
msgid "Creating a Limited Directory Layout in the LFS Filesystem"
msgstr "제한된 디렉터리 레이아웃을 LFS 파일 시스템에 생성하기"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/creatingminlayout.xml:13
msgid ""
"In this section, we begin populating the LFS filesystem with the pieces that "
"will constitute the final Linux system. The first step is to create a "
"limited directory hierarchy, so that the programs compiled in <xref "
"linkend=\"chapter-temporary-tools\"/> (as well as glibc and libstdc++ in "
"<xref linkend=\"chapter-cross-tools\"/>) can be installed in their final "
"location. We do this so those temporary programs will be overwritten when "
"the final versions are built in <xref linkend=\"chapter-building-system\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/creatingminlayout.xml:21
msgid ""
"Create the required directory layout by issuing the following commands as "
"<systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem>:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter04/creatingminlayout.xml:24
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>mkdir -pv $LFS/{etc,var} $LFS/usr/{bin,lib,sbin}\n"
"\n"
"for i in bin lib sbin; do\n"
"  ln -sv usr/$i $LFS/$i\n"
"done\n"
"\n"
"case $(uname -m) in\n"
"  x86_64) mkdir -pv $LFS/lib64 ;;\n"
"esac</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/creatingminlayout.xml:34
msgid ""
"Programs in <xref linkend=\"chapter-temporary-tools\"/> will be compiled "
"with a cross-compiler (more details can be found in section <xref "
"linkend=\"ch-tools-toolchaintechnotes\"/>). This cross-compiler will be "
"installed in a special directory, to separate it from the other programs. "
"Still acting as &root;, create that directory with this command:"
msgstr ""
"Programs in <xref linkend=\"chapter-temporary-tools\"/> will be compiled "
"with a cross-compiler (more details can be found in section <xref "
"linkend=\"ch-tools-toolchaintechnotes\"/>). This cross-compiler will be "
"installed in a special directory, to separate it from the other programs. "
"Still acting as &root;, create that directory with this command:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter04/creatingminlayout.xml:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>mkdir -pv $LFS/tools</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><note><para>
#: en/chapter04/creatingminlayout.xml:44
msgid ""
"The LFS editors have deliberately decided not to use a <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/usr/lib64</filename> directory.  Several steps are "
"taken to be sure the toolchain will not use it. If for any reason this "
"directory appears (either because you made an error in following the "
"instructions, or because you installed a binary package that created it "
"after finishing LFS), it may break your system.  You should always be sure "
"this directory does not exist."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/introduction.xml:13
msgid ""
"In this chapter, we will perform a few additional tasks to prepare for "
"building the temporary system. We will create a set of directories in "
"<filename class=\"directory\">$LFS</filename> (in which we will install the "
"temporary tools), add an unprivileged user, and create an appropriate build "
"environment for that user. We will also explain the units of time "
"(<quote>SBUs</quote>) we use to measure how long it takes to build LFS "
"packages, and provide some information about package test suites."
msgstr ""
"이번 장에서는 임시 시스템을 구축하기 위한 몇 가지 추가 준비 작업을 수행합니"
"다. 임시 도구들을 설치할 <filename class=\"directory\">$LFS</filename> 내에 "
"일련의 디렉터리를 생성하고, 권한이 제한된 사용자를 추가하며, 해당 사용자를 위"
"한 적절한 빌드 환경을 구축할 것입니다. 또한 LFS 패키지를 빌드하는 데 걸리는 "
"시간을 측정하는 단위 <quote>SBUs</quote>에 대해 설명하고, 패키지 테스트 스위"
"트에 대한 정보도 제공합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:11
msgid "Setting Up the Environment"
msgstr "환경 설정하기"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:13
msgid ""
"Set up a good working environment by creating two new startup files for the "
"<command>bash</command> shell. While logged in as user <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem>, issue the following command to create a "
"new <filename>.bash_profile</filename>:"
msgstr ""
"<command>bash</command> 셸 용 새 시작 파일 2개를 생성하여 원활한 작업 환경을 "
"설정하십시오. <systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem> 사용자로 로그인"
"한 동안, 다음 명령어를 실행하여 새 <filename>.bash_profile</filename>을 생성:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:18
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; ~/.bash_profile &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal>exec env -i HOME=$HOME TERM=$TERM PS1='\\u:\\w\\$ ' /bin/bash</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; ~/.bash_profile &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal>exec env -i HOME=$HOME TERM=$TERM PS1='\\u:\\w\\$ ' /bin/bash</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:22
msgid ""
"When logged on as user <systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem>, or "
"when switched to the &lfs-user; user using an <command>su</command> command "
"with the <quote><parameter>-</parameter></quote> option, the initial shell "
"is a <emphasis>login</emphasis> shell which reads the <filename>/etc/"
"profile</filename> of the host (probably containing some settings and "
"environment variables) and then <filename>.bash_profile</filename>.  The "
"<command>exec env -i.../bin/bash</command> command in the "
"<filename>.bash_profile</filename> file replaces the running shell with a "
"new one with a completely empty environment, except for the <envar>HOME</"
"envar>, <envar>TERM</envar>, and <envar>PS1</envar> variables. This ensures "
"that no unwanted and potentially hazardous environment variables from the "
"host system leak into the build environment."
msgstr ""
"<systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem> 사용자로 로그인하거나, "
"<quote><parameter>-</parameter></quote> 옵션을 사용한 <command>su</command> "
"명령으로 &lfs-user; 사용자로 전환했을 때, 초기 셸은 호스트의 <filename>/etc/"
"profile</filename>(아마도 몇몇 설정과 환경 변수를 포함하고 있을 것임)과 "
"<filename>.bash_profile</filename>을 읽어 들이는 <emphasis>login</emphasis> "
"셸이 됩니다. <filename>.bash_profile</filename> 파일 내의 <command>exec env "
"-i.../bin/bash</command> 명령은 실행 중인 셸을 <envar>HOME</envar>, "
"<envar>TERM</envar>, <envar>PS1</envar> 변수를 제외하고 환경이 완전히 비어 있"
"는 새로운 셸로 대체합니다. 이는 호스트 시스템으로부터 원치 않거나 잠재적으로 "
"위험한 환경 변수들이 빌드 환경으로 스며들지 않도록 보장합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:35
msgid ""
"The new instance of the shell is a <emphasis>non-login</emphasis> shell, "
"which does not read, and execute, the contents of the <filename>/etc/"
"profile</filename> or <filename>.bash_profile</filename> files, but rather "
"reads, and executes, the <filename>.bashrc</filename> file instead. Create "
"the <filename>.bashrc</filename> file now:"
msgstr ""
"셸의 새 인스턴스는 <emphasis>non-login</emphasis> 셸이며, 이는 <filename>/"
"etc/profile</filename>이나 <filename>.bash_profile</filename> 파일의 내용을 "
"읽고 실행하지 않는 대신 <filename>.bashrc</filename> 파일을 읽고 실행합니다. "
"이제 <filename>.bashrc</filename> 파일을 생성:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:41
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; ~/.bashrc &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal>set +h\n"
"umask 022\n"
"LFS=/mnt/lfs\n"
"LC_ALL=POSIX\n"
"LFS_TGT=$(uname -m)-lfs-linux-gnu\n"
"PATH=/usr/bin\n"
"if [ ! -L /bin ]; then PATH=/bin:$PATH; fi\n"
"PATH=$LFS/tools/bin:$PATH\n"
"CONFIG_SITE=$LFS/usr/share/config.site\n"
"export LFS LC_ALL LFS_TGT PATH CONFIG_SITE</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; ~/.bashrc &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal>set +h\n"
"umask 022\n"
"LFS=/mnt/lfs\n"
"LC_ALL=POSIX\n"
"LFS_TGT=$(uname -m)-lfs-linux-gnu\n"
"PATH=/usr/bin\n"
"if [ ! -L /bin ]; then PATH=/bin:$PATH; fi\n"
"PATH=$LFS/tools/bin:$PATH\n"
"CONFIG_SITE=$LFS/usr/share/config.site\n"
"export LFS LC_ALL LFS_TGT PATH CONFIG_SITE</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><title>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:55
msgid "The meaning of the settings in <filename>.bashrc</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:58
msgid "<parameter>set +h</parameter>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:60
msgid ""
"The <command>set +h</command> command turns off <command>bash</command>'s "
"hash function. Hashing is ordinarily a useful feature&mdash;<command>bash</"
"command> uses a hash table to remember the full path to executable files to "
"avoid searching the <envar>PATH</envar> time and again to find the same "
"executable. However, the new tools should be used as soon as they are "
"installed. Switching off the hash function forces the shell to search the "
"<envar>PATH</envar> whenever a program is to be run. As such, the shell will "
"find the newly compiled tools in <filename class=\"directory\">$LFS/tools/"
"bin</filename> as soon as they are available without remembering a previous "
"version of the same program provided by the host distro, in <filename "
"class='directory'>/usr/bin</filename> or <filename class='directory'>/bin</"
"filename>."
msgstr ""
"<command>set +h</command> 명령어는 <command>bash</command>의 해시(hash) 기능"
"을 끕니다. 해싱은 보통 유용한 기능입니다. <command>bash</command>는 동일한 실"
"행 파일을 찾기 위해 매번 <envar>PATH</envar>를 반복해서 검색하는 것을 피하려"
"고, 실행 파일의 전체 경로를 기억하는 해시 테이블을 사용합니다. 하지만 새로운 "
"도구는 설치 즉시 사용되어야 합니다. 해시 기능을 끄면 프로그램을 실행할 때마"
"다 셸이 <envar>PATH</envar>를 강제로 검색하게 됩니다. 따라서 셸은 호스트 배포"
"판이 <filename class='directory'>/usr/bin</filename>이나 <filename "
"class='directory'>/bin</filename>에 제공했던 이전 버전의 프로그램을 기억하지 "
"않고, <filename class=\"directory\">$LFS/tools/bin</filename>에 새로 컴파일"
"된 도구가 준비되는 즉시 찾아낼 것입니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:77
msgid "<parameter>umask 022</parameter>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:79
msgid ""
"Setting the umask as we've already explained in <xref linkend='ch-"
"partitioning-aboutlfs' role='.'/>"
msgstr ""
"이미 <xref linkend='ch-partitioning-aboutlfs' role='.'/>에서 설명한 대로 "
"umask를 설정"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:85
msgid "<parameter>LFS=/mnt/lfs</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>LFS=/mnt/lfs</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:87
msgid ""
"The <envar>LFS</envar> variable should be set to the chosen mount point."
msgstr "<envar>LFS</envar> 변수는 선택한 마운트 포인트로 설정되어야 합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:93
msgid "<parameter>LC_ALL=POSIX</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>LC_ALL=POSIX</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:95
msgid ""
"The <envar>LC_ALL</envar> variable controls the localization of certain "
"programs, making their messages follow the conventions of a specified "
"country.  Setting <envar>LC_ALL</envar> to <quote>POSIX</quote> or <quote>C</"
"quote> (the two are equivalent) ensures that everything will work as "
"expected in the cross-compilation environment."
msgstr ""
"<envar>LC_ALL</envar> 변수는 특정 프로그램의 로컬라이제이션을 제어하여, 프로"
"그램의 메시지가 지정된 국가의 관습을 따르게 만듭니다. <envar>LC_ALL</envar>"
"을 <quote>POSIX</quote> 또는 <quote>C</quote>(둘은 마찬가지)로 설정하면 교차 "
"컴파일(cross-compilation) 환경에서 모든 것이 예상대로 작동하도록 보장합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:104
msgid "<parameter>LFS_TGT=$(uname -m)-lfs-linux-gnu</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>LFS_TGT=$(uname -m)-lfs-linux-gnu</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:106
msgid ""
"The <envar>LFS_TGT</envar> variable sets a non-default, but compatible "
"machine description for use when building our cross-compiler and linker and "
"when cross-compiling our temporary toolchain. More information is provided "
"by <xref linkend=\"ch-tools-toolchaintechnotes\" role=\"\"/>."
msgstr ""
"<envar>LFS_TGT</envar> 변수는 우리의 교차 컴파일러(cross-compiler)와 링커를 "
"빌드할 때, 그리고 임시 툴체인을 교차 컴파일할 때 사용할 기본값이 아니면서도 "
"호환 가능한 기기 설명(machine description)을 설정합니다. 더 자세한 정보는 "
"<xref linkend=\"ch-tools-toolchaintechnotes\" role=\"\"/>에서 제공됩니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:114
msgid "<parameter>PATH=/usr/bin</parameter>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:116
msgid ""
"Many modern Linux distributions have merged <filename class=\"directory\">/"
"bin</filename> and <filename class=\"directory\">/usr/bin</filename>. When "
"this is the case, the standard <envar>PATH</envar> variable should be set to "
"<filename class=\"directory\">/usr/bin/</filename> for the <xref "
"linkend=\"chapter-temporary-tools\"/> environment. When this is not the "
"case, the following line adds <filename class=\"directory\">/bin</filename> "
"to the path."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:128
msgid "<parameter>if [ ! -L /bin ]; then PATH=/bin:$PATH; fi</parameter>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:130
msgid ""
"If <filename class=\"directory\">/bin</filename> is not a symbolic link, it "
"must be added to the <envar>PATH</envar> variable."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:136
msgid "<parameter>PATH=$LFS/tools/bin:$PATH</parameter>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:138
msgid ""
"By putting <filename class=\"directory\">$LFS/tools/bin</filename> ahead of "
"the standard <envar>PATH</envar>, the cross-compiler installed at the "
"beginning of <xref linkend=\"chapter-cross-tools\"/> is picked up by the "
"shell immediately after its installation. This, combined with turning off "
"hashing, limits the risk that the compiler from the host is used instead of "
"the cross-compiler."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:148
msgid "<parameter>CONFIG_SITE=$LFS/usr/share/config.site</parameter>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:150
msgid ""
"In <xref linkend=\"chapter-cross-tools\"/> and <xref linkend=\"chapter-"
"temporary-tools\"/>, if this variable is not set, <command>configure</"
"command> scripts may attempt to load configuration items specific to some "
"distributions from <filename>/usr/share/config.site</filename> on the host "
"system. Override it to prevent potential contamination from the host."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:160
msgid "<parameter>export ...</parameter>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:162
msgid ""
"While the preceding commands have set some variables, in order to make them "
"visible within any sub-shells, we export them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><important><para>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:171
msgid ""
"Several commercial distributions add an undocumented instantiation of "
"<filename>/etc/bash.bashrc</filename> to the initialization of "
"<command>bash</command>. This file has the potential to modify the "
"<systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem> user's environment in ways "
"that can affect the building of critical LFS packages. To make sure the "
"<systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem> user's environment is clean, "
"check for the presence of <filename>/etc/bash.bashrc</filename> and, if "
"present, move it out of the way.  As the <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user, run:"
msgstr ""
"여러 상용 배포판은 <command>bash</command>의 초기화 과정에 문서화되지 않은 "
"<filename>/etc/bash.bashrc</filename> 인스턴스를 추가합니다. 이 파일은 중요"
"한 LFS 패키지의 빌드에 영향을 줄 수 있는 방식으로 <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem> 사용자의 환경을 수정할 잠재적 가능성이 있"
"습니다. <systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem> 사용자의 환경이 깨끗"
"한지 확인하기 위해, <filename>/etc/bash.bashrc</filename>가 존재하는지 점검하"
"고 만약 존재한다면 다른 곳으로 옮겨 두십시오. <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem> 사용자로 실행:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><important><screen>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:182
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>[ ! -e /etc/bash.bashrc ] || mv -v /etc/bash.bashrc /etc/bash.bashrc.NOUSE</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>[ ! -e /etc/bash.bashrc ] || mv -v /etc/bash.bashrc /etc/bash.bashrc.NOUSE</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><important><para>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:184
msgid ""
"When the <systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem> user is no longer "
"needed (at the beginning of <xref linkend=\"chapter-chroot-temporary-tools\"/"
">), you may safely restore <filename>/etc/bash.bashrc</filename> (if "
"desired)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><important><para>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:189
msgid ""
"Note that the LFS Bash package we will build in <xref linkend=\"ch-system-"
"bash\"/> is not configured to load or execute <filename>/etc/bash.bashrc</"
"filename>, so this file is useless on a completed LFS system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:196
msgid ""
"For many modern systems with multiple processors (or cores) the compilation "
"time for a package can be reduced by performing a \"parallel make\" by "
"telling the make program how many processors are available via a command "
"line option or an environment variable.  For instance, an Intel Core "
"i9-13900K processor has 8 P (performance) cores and 16 E (efficiency) cores, "
"and a P core can simultaneously run two threads so each P core are modeled "
"as two logical cores by the Linux kernel.  As the result there are 32 "
"logical cores in total.  One obvious way to use all these logical cores is "
"allowing <command>make</command> to spawn up to 32 build jobs.  This can be "
"done by passing the <parameter>-j32</parameter> option to <command>make</"
"command>:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:209
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>make -j32</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:212
msgid ""
"Or set the <envar>MAKEFLAGS</envar> environment variable and its content "
"will be automatically used by <command>make</command> as command line "
"options:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:217
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>export MAKEFLAGS=-j32</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><important><para>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:221
msgid ""
"Never pass a <parameter>-j</parameter> option without a number to "
"<command>make</command> or set such an option in <envar>MAKEFLAGS</envar>.  "
"Doing so will allow <command>make</command> to spawn infinite build jobs and "
"cause system stability problems."
msgstr ""
"<command>make</command>에 숫자 없는 <parameter>-j</parameter> 옵션을 절대 전"
"달하지 말고, <envar>MAKEFLAGS</envar>에도 해당 옵션을 설정하지 마십시오. 그렇"
"게 하면 <command>make</command>가 무한한 빌드 작업을 생성하여 시스템 안정성 "
"문제를 일으킬 수 있습니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:229
msgid ""
"To use all logical cores available for building packages in <xref "
"linkend='chapter-cross-tools'/> and <xref linkend='chapter-temporary-tools'/"
">, set <envar>MAKEFLAGS</envar> now in <filename>.bashrc</filename>:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:235
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt;&gt; ~/.bashrc &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal>export MAKEFLAGS=-j<replaceable>$(nproc)</replaceable></literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:240
msgid ""
"Replace <replaceable>$(nproc)</replaceable> with the number of logical cores "
"you want to use if you don't want to use all the logical cores."
msgstr ""
"Replace <replaceable>$(nproc)</replaceable> with the number of logical cores "
"you want to use if you don't want to use all the logical cores."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:244
msgid ""
"Finally, to ensure the environment is fully prepared for building the "
"temporary tools, force the <command>bash</command> shell to read the new "
"user profile:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter04/settingenviron.xml:248
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>source ~/.bash_profile</userinput>"
msgstr ""

