msgstr "&gcc-tmpp2-du;"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/chapter06/gcc-pass2.xml:44 en/chapter08/gcc.xml:42
msgid "Installation of GCC"
msgstr "Installation of GCC"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter06/gcc-pass2.xml:46
msgid ""
"As in the first build of GCC, the GMP, MPFR, and MPC packages are required. "
"Unpack the tarballs and move them into the required directories:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter06/gcc-pass2.xml:56
msgid ""
"If you are building on x86_64, change the default directory name for 64-bit "
"libraries to <quote>lib</quote>:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter06/gcc-pass2.xml:59 en/chapter08/gcc.xml:51
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput remap=\"pre\">case $(uname -m) in\n"
"  x86_64)\n"
"    sed -e '/m64=/s/lib64/lib/' \\\n"
"        -i.orig gcc/config/i386/t-linux64\n"
"  ;;\n"
"esac</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter06/gcc-pass2.xml:66
msgid ""
"Override the build rules of the libgcc and libstdc++ headers to allow "
"building these libraries with POSIX threads support:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter06/gcc-pass2.xml:69
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput remap=\"pre\">sed '/thread_header =/s/@.*@/gthr-posix.h/' \\\n"
"    -i libgcc/Makefile.in libstdc++-v3/include/Makefile.in</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter06/gcc-pass2.xml:77
msgid ""
"Before starting to build GCC, remember to unset any environment variables "
"that override the default optimization flags."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter06/gcc-pass2.xml:80
msgid "Now prepare GCC for compilation:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter06/gcc-pass2.xml:82
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput remap=\"configure\">../configure                   \\\n"
"    --build=$(../config.guess) \\\n"
"    --host=$LFS_TGT            \\\n"
"    --target=$LFS_TGT          \\\n"
"    --prefix=/usr              \\\n"
"    --with-build-sysroot=$LFS  \\\n"
"    --enable-default-pie       \\\n"
"    --enable-default-ssp       \\\n"
"    --disable-nls              \\\n"
"    --disable-multilib         \\\n"
"    --disable-libatomic        \\\n"
"    --disable-libgomp          \\\n"
"    --disable-libquadmath      \\\n"
"    --disable-libsanitizer     \\\n"
"    --disable-libssp           \\\n"
"    --disable-libvtv           \\\n"
"    --enable-languages=c,c++   \\\n"
"    LDFLAGS_FOR_TARGET=-L$PWD/$LFS_TGT/libgcc</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter06/gcc-pass2.xml:105
msgid "<parameter>--with-build-sysroot=$LFS</parameter>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter06/gcc-pass2.xml:107
msgid ""
"Normally, using <parameter>--host</parameter> ensures that a cross-compiler "
"is used for building GCC, and that compiler knows that it has to look for "
"headers and libraries in <filename class=\"directory\">$LFS</filename>. "
"However, the build system for GCC uses additional tools which are not aware "
"of this location. This switch is needed so those tools will find the needed "
"files in <filename class=\"directory\">$LFS</filename>, and not on the host."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter06/gcc-pass2.xml:118
msgid "<parameter>--target=$LFS_TGT</parameter>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter06/gcc-pass2.xml:120
msgid ""
"We are cross-compiling GCC, so it's impossible to build target libraries "
"(<filename class=\"libraryfile\">libgcc</filename> and <filename "
"class=\"libraryfile\">libstdc++</filename>) with the GCC binaries compiled "
"in this pass&mdash;those binaries won't run on the host.  The GCC build "
"system will attempt to use the host's C and C++ compilers as a workaround by "
"default.  Building the GCC target libraries with a different version of GCC "
"is not supported, so using the host's compilers may cause the build to fail. "
"This parameter ensures the libraries are built by GCC pass 1."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter06/gcc-pass2.xml:134
msgid "<parameter>LDFLAGS_FOR_TARGET=...</parameter>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter06/gcc-pass2.xml:136
msgid ""
"Allow <filename class=\"libraryfile\">libstdc++</filename> to use the "
"<filename class=\"libraryfile\">libgcc</filename> being built in this pass, "
"instead of the previous version built in <xref linkend='ch-tools-gcc-pass1'/"
">.  The previous version cannot properly support C++ exception handling "
"because it was built without libc support."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter06/gcc-pass2.xml:146
msgid "<parameter>--disable-libsanitizer</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>--disable-libsanitizer</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter06/gcc-pass2.xml:148
msgid ""
"Disable GCC sanitizer runtime libraries.  They are not needed for the "
"temporary installation.  In <xref linkend='ch-tools-gcc-pass1'/> it was "
"implied by <parameter>--disable-libstdcxx</parameter>, and now we can "
"explicitly pass it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter06/gcc-pass2.xml:166
msgid ""
"As a finishing touch, create a utility symlink. Many programs and scripts "
"run <command>cc</command> instead of <command>gcc</command>, which is used "
"to keep programs generic and therefore usable on all kinds of UNIX systems "
"where the GNU C compiler is not always installed. Running <command>cc</"
"command> leaves the system administrator free to decide which C compiler to "
"install:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter06/gcc-pass2.xml:173
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput remap=\"install\">ln -sv gcc $LFS/usr/bin/cc</userinput>"
msgstr ""

