#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/chapter07/changingowner.xml:11
msgid "Changing Ownership"
msgstr "소유권 변경"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><note><para>
#: en/chapter07/changingowner.xml:14
msgid ""
"The commands in the remainder of this book must be performed while logged in "
"as user <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> and no longer as "
"user <systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem>. Also, double check "
"that <envar>$LFS</envar> is set in <systemitem class=\"username\">root</"
"systemitem>'s environment."
msgstr ""
"이 책의 남은 부분에 나오는 명령어들은 더 이상 <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem> 사용자가 아닌 <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem> 사용자로 로그인하여 수행해야 합니다. 또"
"한, <envar>$LFS</envar> 변수가 <systemitem class=\"username\">root</"
"systemitem>의 환경에 설정되어 있는지 다시 한번 확인하십시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/changingowner.xml:21
msgid ""
"Currently, the whole directory hierarchy in <filename "
"class=\"directory\">$LFS</filename> is owned by the user <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem>, a user that exists only on the host "
"system. If the directories and files under <filename "
"class=\"directory\">$LFS</filename> are kept as they are, they will be owned "
"by a user ID without a corresponding account. This is dangerous because a "
"user account created later could get this same user ID and would own all the "
"files under <filename class=\"directory\">$LFS</filename>, thus exposing "
"these files to possible malicious manipulation."
msgstr ""
"Currently, the whole directory hierarchy in <filename "
"class=\"directory\">$LFS</filename> is owned by the user <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem>, a user that exists only on the host "
"system. If the directories and files under <filename "
"class=\"directory\">$LFS</filename> are kept as they are, they will be owned "
"by a user ID without a corresponding account. This is dangerous because a "
"user account created later could get this same user ID and would own all the "
"files under <filename class=\"directory\">$LFS</filename>, thus exposing "
"these files to possible malicious manipulation."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/changingowner.xml:31
msgid ""
"To address this issue, change the ownership of the <filename "
"class=\"directory\">$LFS/*</filename> directories to user <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem> by running the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter07/changingowner.xml:36
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>chown --from &lfs-username; -R root:root $LFS/{usr,var,etc,tools}\n"
"case $(uname -m) in\n"
"  x86_64) chown --from &lfs-username; -R root:root $LFS/lib64 ;;\n"
"esac</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'xreflabel' of: <chapter>
#: en/chapter07/chapter07.xml:8
msgid "Chapter&nbsp;7"
msgstr "제7장"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><title>
#: en/chapter07/chapter07.xml:12
msgid "Entering Chroot and Building Additional Temporary Tools"
msgstr "Chroot 진입 및 추가 임시 도구 빌드하기"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/chapter07/chroot.xml:11
msgid "Entering the Chroot Environment"
msgstr "Chroot 환경 진입"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/chroot.xml:13
msgid ""
"Now that all the packages which are required to build the rest of the needed "
"tools are on the system, it is time to enter the chroot environment and "
"finish installing the temporary tools. This environment will also be used to "
"install the final system. As user <systemitem class=\"username\">root</"
"systemitem>, run the following command to enter the environment that is, at "
"the moment, populated with nothing but temporary tools:"
msgstr ""
"이제, 필요한 나머지 도구들을 빌드하는 데 필요한 모든 패키지가 시스템에 갖춰졌"
"으므로, chroot 환경으로 진입하여 임시 도구 설치를 마무리할 차례입니다. 이 환"
"경은 최종 시스템을 구축하는 데에도 사용될 것입니다. 현재는 임시 도구들만 들"
"어 있는 이 환경에 진입하기 위해, <systemitem class=\"username\">root</"
"systemitem> 사용자로 다음 명령어를 실행:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter07/chroot.xml:21
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>chroot \"$LFS\" /usr/bin/env -i   \\\n"
"    HOME=/root                  \\\n"
"    TERM=\"$TERM\"                \\\n"
"    PS1='(lfs chroot) \\u:\\w\\$ ' \\\n"
"    PATH=/usr/bin:/usr/sbin     \\\n"
"    MAKEFLAGS=\"-j<replaceable>$(nproc)</replaceable>\"      \\\n"
"    TESTSUITEFLAGS=\"-j<replaceable>$(nproc)</replaceable>\" \\\n"
"    /bin/bash --login</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>chroot \"$LFS\" /usr/bin/env -i   \\\n"
"    HOME=/root                  \\\n"
"    TERM=\"$TERM\"                \\\n"
"    PS1='(lfs chroot) \\u:\\w\\$ ' \\\n"
"    PATH=/usr/bin:/usr/sbin     \\\n"
"    MAKEFLAGS=\"-j<replaceable>$(nproc)</replaceable>\"      \\\n"
"    TESTSUITEFLAGS=\"-j<replaceable>$(nproc)</replaceable>\" \\\n"
"    /bin/bash --login</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/chroot.xml:31
msgid ""
"If you don't want to use all available logical cores, replace <replaceable>$"
"(nproc)</replaceable> with the number of logical cores you want to use for "
"building packages in this chapter and the following chapters.  The test "
"suites of some packages (notably Autoconf, Libtool, and Tar) in &ch-final; "
"are not affected by <envar>MAKEFLAGS</envar>, they use a "
"<envar>TESTSUITEFLAGS</envar> environment variable instead. We set that here "
"as well for running these test suites with multiple cores."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/chroot.xml:40
msgid ""
"The <parameter>-i</parameter> option given to the <command>env</command> "
"command will clear all the variables in the chroot environment. After that, "
"only the <envar>HOME</envar>, <envar>TERM</envar>, <envar>PS1</envar>, and "
"<envar>PATH</envar> variables are set again. The <parameter>TERM=$TERM</"
"parameter> construct sets the <envar>TERM</envar> variable inside chroot to "
"the same value as outside chroot. This variable is needed so programs like "
"<command>vim</command> and <command>less</command> can operate properly.  If "
"other variables are desired, such as <envar>CFLAGS</envar> or "
"<envar>CXXFLAGS</envar>, this is a good place to set them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/chroot.xml:51
msgid ""
"From this point on, there is no need to use the <envar>LFS</envar> variable "
"any more because all work will be restricted to the LFS file system; the "
"<command>chroot</command> command runs the Bash shell with the root "
"(<filename class=\"directory\">/</filename>) directory set to <filename "
"class='directory'>$LFS</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/chroot.xml:58
msgid ""
"Notice that <filename class=\"directory\">/tools/bin</filename> is not in "
"the <envar>PATH</envar>. This means that the cross toolchain will no longer "
"be used."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/chroot.xml:62
msgid ""
"Also note that the <command>bash</command> prompt will say <computeroutput>I "
"have no name!</computeroutput> This is normal because the <filename>/etc/"
"passwd</filename> file has not been created yet."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><note><para>
#: en/chapter07/chroot.xml:67
msgid ""
"It is important that all the commands throughout the remainder of this "
"chapter and the following chapters are run from within the chroot "
"environment. If you leave this environment for any reason (rebooting for "
"example), ensure that the virtual kernel filesystems are mounted as "
"explained in <xref linkend=\"ch-tools-bindmount\"/> and <xref linkend=\"ch-"
"tools-kernfsmount\"/> and enter chroot again before continuing with the "
"installation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:11
msgid "Cleaning up and Saving the Temporary System"
msgstr "임시 시스템 정리 및 저장"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:14
msgid "Cleaning"
msgstr "정리"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:16
msgid ""
"First, remove the currently installed documentation files to prevent them "
"from ending up in the final system, and to save about 35 MB:"
msgstr ""
"첫째, 현재 설치된 문서 파일들이 최종 시스템에 포함되는 것을 막고 약 35 MB 용"
"량 절약을 위해 이들을 삭제:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>rm -rf /usr/share/{info,man,doc}/*</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>rm -rf /usr/share/{info,man,doc}/*</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:21
msgid ""
"Second, on a modern Linux system, the libtool .la files are only useful for "
"libltdl.  No libraries in LFS are loaded by libltdl, and it's known that "
"some .la files can cause BLFS package failures.  Remove those files now:"
msgstr ""
"둘째, 현대적인 리눅스 시스템에서 libtool의 .la 파일들은 오직 libltdl을 위해서"
"만 유용합니다. LFS의 라이브러리 중에서 libltdl에 의해 로드되는 것은 없으며, "
"일부 .la 파일들은 BLFS 패키지 빌드 실패를 일으키는 것으로 알려져 있습니다. 이"
"제 이 파일들을 삭제:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>find /usr/{lib,libexec} -name \\*.la -delete</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>find /usr/{lib,libexec} -name \\*.la -delete</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:29
msgid ""
"The current system size is now about 3 GB, however the /tools directory is "
"no longer needed. It uses about 1 GB of disk space.  Delete it now:"
msgstr ""
"현재 시스템 크기는 약 3GB이지만, /tools 디렉터리는 더 이상 필요 없습니다. 그"
"것은 약 1GB 디스크 공간을 씁니다. 지금 삭제:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:34
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>rm -rf /tools</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>rm -rf /tools</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:38
msgid "Backup"
msgstr "Backup"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:41
msgid ""
"At this point the essential programs and libraries have been created and "
"your current LFS system is in a good state. Your system can now be backed up "
"for later reuse. In case of fatal failures in the subsequent chapters, it "
"often turns out that removing everything and starting over (more carefully) "
"is the best way to recover. Unfortunately, all the temporary files will be "
"removed, too. To avoid spending extra time to redo something which has been "
"done successfully, creating a backup of the current LFS system may prove "
"useful."
msgstr ""
"이 시점에서 필수적인 프로그램과 라이브러리들이 생성되었으며, 현재 우리의 LFS "
"시스템은 좋은 상태입니다. 이제 나중에 다시 사용하기 위해 시스템을 백업할 수 "
"있습니다. 이후의 장에서 치명적인 오류가 발생할 경우, 모든 것을 삭제하고 (더 "
"주의 깊게) 다시 시작하는 것이 복구를 위한 가장 좋은 방법인 경우가 많습니다. "
"불행하게도, 이 과정에서 모든 임시 파일 또한 삭제될 것입니다. 이미 성공적으로 "
"완료한 작업을 다시 수행하느라 추가적인 시간을 낭비하지 않도록, 현재 LFS 시스"
"템의 백업본을 구축해 두는 것이 유용할 수 있습니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:52
msgid ""
"All the remaining steps in this section are optional. Nevertheless, as soon "
"as you begin installing packages in <xref linkend=\"chapter-building-"
"system\"/>, the temporary files will be overwritten. So it may be a good "
"idea to do a backup of the current system as described below."
msgstr ""
"이 절 나머지 모든 단계는 선택사항입니다. 그럼에도, <xref linkend=\"chapter-"
"building-system\"/>에서 패키지 설치를 시작하는 즉시 임시 파일들이 덮어씌워질 "
"것입니다. 따라서, 아래에 설명된 대로 현재 시스템을 백업해 두는 것이 좋은 방법"
"일 겁니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:60
msgid ""
"The following steps are performed from outside the chroot environment. That "
"means you have to leave the chroot environment first before continuing. The "
"reason for that is to get access to file system locations outside of the "
"chroot environment to store/read the backup archive, which ought not be "
"placed within the <filename class=\"directory\">$LFS</filename> hierarchy."
msgstr ""
"다음 단계는 chroot 환경 밖에서 수행됩니다. 즉, 계속 진행하기 전에 먼저 "
"chroot 환경을 벗어나야 합니다. 그 이유는 <filename class=\"directory\">$LFS</"
"filename> 계층에 두어서는 안 되는 백업 아카이브를 저장하거나 읽으려면, "
"chroot 환경 밖의 파일 시스템 위치에 접근해야 하기 때문."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:70
msgid "If you have decided to make a backup, leave the chroot environment:"
msgstr "백업을 하기로 결정했다면, chroot 환경을 벗어나기:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:73
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>exit</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>exit</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><important><para>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:77
msgid ""
"All of the following instructions are executed by <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem> on your host system.  Take extra care "
"about the commands you're going to run as mistakes made here can modify your "
"host system. Be aware that the environment variable <envar>LFS</envar> is "
"set for user <systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem> by default but "
"may <emphasis>not</emphasis> be set for <systemitem class=\"username\">root</"
"systemitem>."
msgstr ""
"다음 모든 지침은 호스트 시스템에서 <systemitem class=\"username\">root</"
"systemitem> 권한으로 실행됩니다. 여기서의 실수는 호스트 시스템을 바꿀 수 있으"
"므로 실행하려는 명령에 특히 주의하십시오. 환경변수 <envar>LFS</envar>는 기본"
"적으로 <systemitem class=\"username\">lfs</systemitem> 사용자에게는 설정되어 "
"있지만, <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> 사용자에게는 설정되"
"어 있지 않을 수 있다는 점에 유의하십시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><important><para>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:87
msgid ""
"Whenever commands are to be executed by <systemitem class=\"username\">root</"
"systemitem>, make sure you have set <envar>LFS</envar>."
msgstr ""
"명령어가 <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem>에 의해 실행되어야 "
"할 때마다, <envar>LFS</envar> 변수가 설정되어 있는지 확인하십시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><important><para>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:91
msgid ""
"This has been discussed in <xref linkend='ch-partitioning-aboutlfs' role='.'/"
">"
msgstr "이것은 <xref linkend='ch-partitioning-aboutlfs' role='.'/> 에서 논의"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:96
msgid "Before making a backup, unmount the virtual file systems:"
msgstr "백업 전, 가상 파일 시스템 언마운트:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:98
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>mountpoint -q $LFS/dev/shm &amp;&amp; umount $LFS/dev/shm\n"
"umount $LFS/dev/pts\n"
"umount $LFS/{sys,proc,run,dev}</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>mountpoint -q $LFS/dev/shm &amp;&amp; umount $LFS/dev/shm\n"
"umount $LFS/dev/pts\n"
"umount $LFS/{sys,proc,run,dev}</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:103
msgid ""
"Make sure you have at least 1 GB free disk space (the source tarballs will "
"be included in the backup archive) on the file system containing the "
"directory where you create the backup archive."
msgstr ""
"백업 아카이브를 생성할 디렉터리가 포함된 파일 시스템에 최소 1GB의 여유 디스"
"크 공간이 있는지 확인하십시오(소스 타르볼(tarball)도 백업 아카이브에 포함될 "
"것입니다)."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:109
msgid ""
"Note that the instructions below specify the home directory of the host "
"system's <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user, which is "
"typically found on the root file system.  Replace <envar>$HOME</envar> by a "
"directory of your choice if you do not want to have the backup stored in "
"<systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem>'s home directory."
msgstr ""
"아래 지침은 호스트 시스템의 <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> "
"사용자 홈 디렉터리를 지정하며, 이는 일반적으로 루트 파일 시스템에서 찾을 수 "
"있음에 유의하십시오. <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> 의 홈 "
"디렉터리에 백업을 저장하고 싶지 않다면, <envar>$HOME</envar>을 원하는 디렉터"
"리로 교체하십시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:118
msgid "Create the backup archive by running the following command:"
msgstr "다음 명령을 실행하여 백업 아카이브 생성:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:123
msgid ""
"Because the backup archive is compressed, it takes a relatively long time "
"(over 10 minutes) even on a reasonably fast system."
msgstr ""
"백업 아카이브가 압축되므로, 꽤 빠른 시스템에서도 상대적으로 긴 시간(10분 이"
"상)이 걸립니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:128
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cd $LFS\n"
"tar -cJpf $HOME/lfs-temp-tools-&version;.tar.xz .</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cd $LFS\n"
"tar -cJpf $HOME/lfs-temp-tools-&version;.tar.xz .</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:133
msgid ""
"If continuing to chapter 8, don't forget to reenter the chroot environment "
"as explained in the <quote>Important</quote> box below."
msgstr ""
"8장으로 계속 진행한다면, 아래의 <quote>중요(Important)</quote> 상자에 설명된 "
"대로 chroot 환경에 재진입 하는 것을 잊지 마십시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:141
msgid "Restore"
msgstr "Restore"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:144
msgid ""
"In case some mistakes have been made and you need to start over, you can use "
"this backup to restore the system and save some recovery time.  Since the "
"sources are located under <filename class=\"directory\">$LFS</filename>, "
"they are included in the backup archive as well, so they do not need to be "
"downloaded again. After checking that <envar>$LFS</envar> is set properly, "
"you can restore the backup by executing the following commands:"
msgstr ""
"실수하여 처음부터 다시 시작해야 하는 경우, 이 백업을 사용하여 시스템을 복구하"
"고 복구 시간을 단축할 수 있습니다. 소스 파일이 <filename "
"class=\"directory\">$LFS</filename> 아래에 위치하므로 백업 아카이브에도 들어 "
"있으며, 따라서 다시 다운로드할 필요가 없습니다. <envar>$LFS</envar>가 올바르"
"게 설정되었는지 확인한 후, 다음 명령을 실행하여 백업을 복구할 수 있습니다:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><warning><para>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:156
msgid ""
"The following commands are extremely dangerous.  If you run <command>rm "
"-rf ./*</command> as the &root; user and you do not change to the $LFS "
"directory or the <envar>LFS</envar> environment variable is not set for the "
"&root; user, it will destroy your entire host system.  YOU ARE WARNED."
msgstr ""
"다음 명령어는 극도로 위험합니다. 만약 &root; 사용자로 <command>rm -rf ./*</"
"command> 명령을 하면서 $LFS 디렉터리로 이동하지 않았거나, &root; 사용자에게 "
"<envar>LFS</envar> 환경 변수가 설정되어 있지 않다면, 여러분의 호스트 시스템 "
"전체가 파괴될 것입니다. 경고 했습니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:162
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<literal>cd $LFS\n"
"rm -rf ./*\n"
"tar -xpf $HOME/lfs-temp-tools-&version;.tar.xz</literal>"
msgstr ""
"<literal>cd $LFS\n"
"rm -rf ./*\n"
"tar -xpf $HOME/lfs-temp-tools-&version;.tar.xz</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:167
msgid ""
"Again, double check that the environment has been set up properly and "
"continue building the rest of the system."
msgstr ""
"다시 한번, 환경이 올바르게 설정되었는지 이중 점검하고 시스템의 나머지 부분을 "
"계속해서 빌드하십시오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><important><para>
#: en/chapter07/cleanup.xml:173
msgid ""
"If you left the chroot environment to create a backup or restart building "
"using a restore, remember to check that the virtual file systems are still "
"mounted (<command>findmnt | grep $LFS</command> should show at least "
"<filename class=\"directory\">$LFS/dev</filename>, <filename "
"class=\"directory\">$LFS/proc</filename>, and <filename "
"class=\"directory\">$LFS/sys</filename> as mounted).  If they are not "
"mounted, remount them now as described in <xref linkend='ch-tools-kernfs'/> "
"and re-enter the chroot environment (see <xref linkend='ch-tools-chroot'/>) "
"before continuing."
msgstr ""
"백업을 생성하기 위해 chroot 환경을 벗어났거나 복구본을 사용하여 빌드를 다시 "
"시작했다면, 가상 파일 시스템들이 여전히 마운트되어 있는지 확인해야 함을 잊지 "
"마십시오 (<command>findmnt | grep $LFS</command> 했을 때 최소한 <filename "
"class=\"directory\">$LFS/dev</filename>, <filename class=\"directory\">$LFS/"
"proc</filename>, 및 <filename class=\"directory\">$LFS/sys</filename>가 마운"
"트된 상태로 표시되어야 합니다). 만약 마운트되어 있지 않다면, <xref "
"linkend='ch-tools-kernfs'/>에 설명된 대로 지금 다시 마운트하고, 계속 진행하"
"기 전에 <xref linkend='ch-tools-chroot'/> 참조하여 chroot 환경에 재진입하십시"
"오."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:11
msgid "Creating Essential Files and Symlinks"
msgstr "필수 파일들과 심볼릭 링크 생성:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><indexterm><primary>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:14
msgid "/etc/passwd"
msgstr "/etc/passwd"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><indexterm><primary>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:18
msgid "/etc/group"
msgstr "/etc/group"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><indexterm><primary>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:22
msgid "/run/utmp"
msgstr "/run/utmp"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><indexterm><primary>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:26
msgid "/var/log/btmp"
msgstr "/var/log/btmp"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><indexterm><primary>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:30
msgid "/var/log/lastlog"
msgstr "/var/log/lastlog"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><indexterm><primary>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:34
msgid "/var/log/wtmp"
msgstr "/var/log/wtmp"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:37
msgid ""
"Historically, Linux maintained a list of the mounted file systems in the "
"file <filename>/etc/mtab</filename>. Modern kernels maintain this list "
"internally and expose it to the user via the <filename class=\"directory\">/"
"proc</filename> filesystem. To satisfy utilities that expect to find "
"<filename>/etc/mtab</filename>, create the following symbolic link:"
msgstr ""
"역사적으로, 리눅스는 마운트된 파일 시스템 목록을 <filename>/etc/mtab</"
"filename> 파일에 유지했습니다. 현대 커널은 이 목록을 내부적으로 유지하며 "
"<filename class=\"directory\">/proc</filename> 파일 시스템을 통해 사용자에게 "
"노출합니다. <filename>/etc/mtab</filename> 파일을 찾을 것으로 예상되는 유틸리"
"티들을 만족시키기 위해, 다음 심볼릭 링크를 생성:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:44
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>ln -sv /proc/self/mounts /etc/mtab</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>ln -sv /proc/self/mounts /etc/mtab</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:46
msgid ""
"Create a basic <filename>/etc/hosts</filename> file to be referenced in some "
"test suites, and in one of Perl's configuration files as well:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:50
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /etc/hosts &lt;&lt; EOF\n"
"<literal>127.0.0.1  localhost $(hostname)\n"
"::1        localhost</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:55
msgid ""
"In order for user <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> to be "
"able to login and for the name <quote>root</quote> to be recognized, there "
"must be relevant entries in the <filename>/etc/passwd</filename> and "
"<filename>/etc/group</filename> files."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:60
msgid ""
"Create the <filename>/etc/passwd</filename> file by running the following "
"command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:63
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /etc/passwd &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal>root:x:0:0:root:/root:/bin/bash\n"
"bin:x:1:1:bin:/dev/null:/usr/bin/false\n"
"daemon:x:6:6:Daemon User:/dev/null:/usr/bin/false\n"
"messagebus:x:18:18:D-Bus Message Daemon User:/run/dbus:/usr/bin/false\n"
"uuidd:x:80:80:UUID Generation Daemon User:/dev/null:/usr/bin/false\n"
"nobody:x:65534:65534:Unprivileged User:/dev/null:/usr/bin/false</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:72
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /etc/passwd &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal>root:x:0:0:root:/root:/bin/bash\n"
"bin:x:1:1:bin:/dev/null:/usr/bin/false\n"
"daemon:x:6:6:Daemon User:/dev/null:/usr/bin/false\n"
"messagebus:x:18:18:D-Bus Message Daemon User:/run/dbus:/usr/bin/false\n"
"systemd-journal-gateway:x:73:73:systemd Journal Gateway:/:/usr/bin/false\n"
"systemd-journal-remote:x:74:74:systemd Journal Remote:/:/usr/bin/false\n"
"systemd-journal-upload:x:75:75:systemd Journal Upload:/:/usr/bin/false\n"
"systemd-network:x:76:76:systemd Network Management:/:/usr/bin/false\n"
"systemd-resolve:x:77:77:systemd Resolver:/:/usr/bin/false\n"
"systemd-timesync:x:78:78:systemd Time Synchronization:/:/usr/bin/false\n"
"systemd-coredump:x:79:79:systemd Core Dumper:/:/usr/bin/false\n"
"uuidd:x:80:80:UUID Generation Daemon User:/dev/null:/usr/bin/false\n"
"systemd-oom:x:81:81:systemd Out Of Memory Daemon:/:/usr/bin/false\n"
"nobody:x:65534:65534:Unprivileged User:/dev/null:/usr/bin/false</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:89
msgid ""
"The actual password for <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> "
"will be set later."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:92
msgid ""
"Create the <filename>/etc/group</filename> file by running the following "
"command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:95
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /etc/group &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal>root:x:0:\n"
"bin:x:1:daemon\n"
"sys:x:2:\n"
"kmem:x:3:\n"
"tape:x:4:\n"
"tty:x:5:\n"
"daemon:x:6:\n"
"floppy:x:7:\n"
"disk:x:8:\n"
"lp:x:9:\n"
"dialout:x:10:\n"
"audio:x:11:\n"
"video:x:12:\n"
"utmp:x:13:\n"
"clock:x:14:\n"
"cdrom:x:15:\n"
"adm:x:16:\n"
"messagebus:x:18:\n"
"input:x:24:\n"
"mail:x:34:\n"
"kvm:x:61:\n"
"uuidd:x:80:\n"
"wheel:x:97:\n"
"users:x:999:\n"
"nogroup:x:65534:</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:123
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /etc/group &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal>root:x:0:\n"
"bin:x:1:daemon\n"
"sys:x:2:\n"
"kmem:x:3:\n"
"tape:x:4:\n"
"tty:x:5:\n"
"daemon:x:6:\n"
"floppy:x:7:\n"
"disk:x:8:\n"
"lp:x:9:\n"
"dialout:x:10:\n"
"audio:x:11:\n"
"video:x:12:\n"
"utmp:x:13:\n"
"clock:x:14:\n"
"cdrom:x:15:\n"
"adm:x:16:\n"
"messagebus:x:18:\n"
"systemd-journal:x:23:\n"
"input:x:24:\n"
"mail:x:34:\n"
"kvm:x:61:\n"
"systemd-journal-gateway:x:73:\n"
"systemd-journal-remote:x:74:\n"
"systemd-journal-upload:x:75:\n"
"systemd-network:x:76:\n"
"systemd-resolve:x:77:\n"
"systemd-timesync:x:78:\n"
"systemd-coredump:x:79:\n"
"uuidd:x:80:\n"
"systemd-oom:x:81:\n"
"wheel:x:97:\n"
"users:x:999:\n"
"nogroup:x:65534:</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:160
msgid ""
"The created groups are not part of any standard&mdash;they are groups "
"decided on in part by the requirements of the Udev configuration in Chapter "
"9, and in part by common conventions employed by a number of existing Linux "
"distributions. In addition, some test suites rely on specific users or "
"groups.  The Linux Standard Base (LSB, available at <ulink url=\"https://"
"refspecs.linuxfoundation.org/lsb.shtml\"/>) only recommends that, besides "
"the group <systemitem class=\"groupname\">root</systemitem> with a Group ID "
"(GID) of 0, a group <systemitem class=\"groupname\">bin</systemitem> with a "
"GID of 1 be present. The GID of 5 is widely used for the <systemitem "
"class=\"groupname\">tty</systemitem> group, and the number 5 is also used in "
"<phrase revision=\"systemd\">systemd</phrase> <phrase "
"revision=\"sysv\"><filename>/etc/fstab</filename></phrase> for the "
"<systemitem class=\"filesystem\">devpts</systemitem> filesystem.  All other "
"group names and GIDs can be chosen freely by the system administrator since "
"well-written programs do not depend on GID numbers, but rather use the "
"group's name."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:177
msgid ""
"The ID 65534 is used by the kernel for NFS and separate user namespaces for "
"unmapped users and groups (those exist on the NFS server or the parent user "
"namespace, but <quote>do not exist</quote> on the local machine or in the "
"separate namespace).  We assign <systemitem class=\"username\">nobody</"
"systemitem> and <systemitem class=\"groupname\">nogroup</systemitem> to "
"avoid an unnamed ID.  But other distros may treat this ID differently, so "
"any portable program should not depend on this assignment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:190
msgid ""
"Some tests in <xref linkend=\"chapter-building-system\"/> need a regular "
"user. We add this user here and delete this account at the end of that "
"chapter."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:194
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>echo \"tester:x:101:101::/home/tester:/bin/bash\" &gt;&gt; /etc/passwd\n"
"echo \"tester:x:101:\" &gt;&gt; /etc/group\n"
"install -o tester -d /home/tester</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:198
msgid ""
"To remove the <quote>I have no name!</quote> prompt, start a new shell. "
"Since the <filename>/etc/passwd</filename> and <filename>/etc/group</"
"filename> files have been created, user name and group name resolution will "
"now work:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:204 en/chapter08/bash.xml:112
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>exec /usr/bin/bash --login</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:206
msgid ""
"The <command>login</command>, <command>agetty</command>, and <command>init</"
"command> programs (and others) use a number of log files to record "
"information such as who was logged into the system and when. However, these "
"programs will not write to the log files if they do not already exist. "
"Initialize the log files and give them proper permissions:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:213
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>touch /var/log/{btmp,lastlog,faillog,wtmp}\n"
"chgrp -v utmp /var/log/lastlog\n"
"chmod -v 664  /var/log/lastlog\n"
"chmod -v 600  /var/log/btmp</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:218
msgid ""
"The <filename>/var/log/wtmp</filename> file records all logins and logouts. "
"The <filename>/var/log/lastlog</filename> file records when each user last "
"logged in. The <filename>/var/log/faillog</filename> file records failed "
"login attempts.  The <filename>/var/log/btmp</filename> file records the bad "
"login attempts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><note><para>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:224
msgid ""
"The <filename>/run/utmp</filename> file records the users that are currently "
"logged in.  <phrase revision='sysv'>This file is created dynamically in the "
"boot scripts.</phrase><phrase revision='systemd'>This file is created "
"dynamically when a user logs into the system.</phrase>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><note><para>
#: en/chapter07/createfiles.xml:235
msgid ""
"The <filename>utmp</filename>, <filename>wtmp</filename>, <filename>btmp</"
"filename>, and <filename>lastlog</filename> files use 32-bit integers for "
"timestamps and they'll be fundamentally broken after year 2038.  Many "
"packages have stopped using them and other packages are going to stop using "
"them.  It is probably best to consider them deprecated."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/chapter07/creatingdirs.xml:11
msgid "Creating Directories"
msgstr "디렉터리 생성"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/creatingdirs.xml:13
msgid ""
"It is time to create the full directory structure in the LFS file system."
msgstr "이제 전체 디렉터리 구조를 LFS 파일 시스템에 생성할 때입니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><note><para>
#: en/chapter07/creatingdirs.xml:15
msgid ""
"Some of the directories mentioned in this section may have already been "
"created earlier with explicit instructions, or when installing some "
"packages.  They are repeated below for completeness."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/creatingdirs.xml:19
msgid ""
"Create some root-level directories that are not in the limited set required "
"in the previous chapters by issuing the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter07/creatingdirs.xml:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>mkdir -pv /{boot,home,mnt,opt,srv}</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/creatingdirs.xml:24
msgid ""
"Create the required set of subdirectories below the root-level by issuing "
"the following commands:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/chapter07/creatingdirs.xml:27
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>mkdir -pv /etc/{opt,sysconfig}\n"
"mkdir -pv /lib/firmware\n"
"mkdir -pv /media/{floppy,cdrom}\n"
"mkdir -pv /usr/{,local/}{include,src}\n"
"mkdir -pv /usr/lib/locale\n"
"mkdir -pv /usr/local/{bin,lib,sbin}\n"
"mkdir -pv /usr/{,local/}share/{color,dict,doc,info,locale,man}\n"
"mkdir -pv /usr/{,local/}share/{misc,terminfo,zoneinfo}\n"
"mkdir -pv /usr/{,local/}share/man/man{1..8}\n"
"mkdir -pv /var/{cache,local,log,mail,opt,spool}\n"
"mkdir -pv /var/lib/{color,misc,locate}\n"
"\n"
"ln -sfv /run /var/run\n"
"ln -sfv /run/lock /var/lock\n"
"\n"
"install -dv -m 0750 /root\n"
"install -dv -m 1777 /tmp /var/tmp</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/creatingdirs.xml:45
msgid ""
"Directories are, by default, created with permission mode 755, but this is "
"not desirable everywhere. In the commands above, two changes are "
"made&mdash;one to the home directory of user <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem>, and another to the directories for "
"temporary files."
msgstr ""
"Directories are, by default, created with permission mode 755, but this is "
"not desirable everywhere. In the commands above, two changes are "
"made&mdash;one to the home directory of user <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem>, and another to the directories for "
"temporary files."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/chapter07/creatingdirs.xml:51
msgid ""
"The first mode change ensures that not just anybody can enter the <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/root</filename> directory&mdash;just like a normal user "
"would do with his or her own home directory. The second mode change makes "
"sure that any user can write to the <filename class=\"directory\">/tmp</"
"filename> and <filename class=\"directory\">/var/tmp</filename> directories, "
"but cannot remove another user's files from them. The latter is prohibited "
"by the so-called <quote>sticky bit,</quote> the highest bit (1) in the 1777 "
"bit mask."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/chapter07/creatingdirs.xml:61
msgid "FHS Compliance Note"
msgstr "FHS Compliance Note"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter07/creatingdirs.xml:63
msgid ""
"This directory tree is based on the Filesystem Hierarchy Standard (FHS) "
"(available at <ulink url=\"https://refspecs.linuxfoundation.org/fhs.shtml\"/"
">).  The FHS also specifies the optional existence of additional directories "
"such as <filename class=\"directory\">/usr/local/games</filename> and "
"<filename class=\"directory\">/usr/share/games</filename>.  In LFS, we "
"create only the directories that are really necessary. However, feel free to "
"create more directories, if you wish."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><warning><para>
#: en/chapter07/creatingdirs.xml:74
msgid ""
"The FHS does not mandate the existence of the directory <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/usr/lib64</filename>, and the LFS editors have decided "
"not to use it. For the instructions in LFS and BLFS to work correctly, it is "
"imperative that this directory be non-existent. From time to time you should "
"verify that it does not exist, because it is easy to create it "
"inadvertently, and this will probably break your system."
msgstr ""

