#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/chapter08/ninja.xml:41
msgid "Installation of Ninja"
msgstr "Installation of Ninja"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/ninja.xml:43
msgid ""
"When run, <command>ninja</command> normally utilizes the greatest possible "
"number of processes in parallel.  By default this is the number of cores on "
"the system, plus two.  This may overheat the CPU, or make the system run out "
"of memory.  When <command>ninja</command> is invoked from the command line, "
"passing the -jN parameter will limit the number of parallel processes. Some "
"packages embed the execution of <command>ninja</command>, and do not pass "
"the -j parameter on to it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para><screen>
#: en/chapter08/ninja.xml:54
#, no-wrap
msgid "export NINJAJOBS=4"
msgstr "export NINJAJOBS=4"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/ninja.xml:50
msgid ""
"Using the <emphasis>optional</emphasis> procedure below allows a user to "
"limit the number of parallel processes via an environment variable, "
"NINJAJOBS.  <emphasis role=\"bold\">For example</emphasis>, setting: "
"<placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/> will limit <command>ninja</command> "
"to four parallel processes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/ninja.xml:58
msgid ""
"If desired, make <command>ninja</command> recognize the environment variable "
"NINJAJOBS by running the stream editor:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter08/ninja.xml:61
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput remap=\"pre\">sed -i '/int Guess/a \\\n"
"  int   j = 0;\\\n"
"  char* jobs = getenv( \"NINJAJOBS\" );\\\n"
"  if ( jobs != NULL ) j = atoi( jobs );\\\n"
"  if ( j > 0 ) return j;\\\n"
"' src/ninja.cc</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/ninja.xml:68
msgid "Build Ninja with:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter08/ninja.xml:70
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput remap=\"configure\">python3 configure.py --bootstrap --verbose</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><title>
#: en/chapter08/ninja.xml:73
msgid "The meaning of the build option:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter08/ninja.xml:76
msgid "<parameter>--bootstrap</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>--bootstrap</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/ninja.xml:78
msgid "This parameter forces Ninja to rebuild itself for the current system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter08/ninja.xml:84
msgid "<parameter>--verbose</parameter>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/ninja.xml:86
msgid ""
"This parameter makes <command>configure.py</command> show the progress "
"building Ninja."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/ninja.xml:93
msgid ""
"The package tests cannot run in the chroot environment. They require <ulink "
"url=\"&blfs-book;general/cmake.html\">cmake</ulink>.  But the basic function "
"of this package is already tested by rebuilding itself (with the "
"<parameter>--bootstrap</parameter> option) anyway."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter08/ninja.xml:106
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput remap=\"install\">install -vm755 ninja /usr/bin/\n"
"install -vDm644 misc/bash-completion /usr/share/bash-completion/completions/ninja\n"
"install -vDm644 misc/zsh-completion  /usr/share/zsh/site-functions/_ninja</userinput>"
msgstr ""

