msgstr "&shadow-fin-du;"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:42
msgid "Installation of Shadow"
msgstr "Installation of Shadow"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><important><para>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:46
msgid ""
"If you've installed Linux-PAM, you should follow <ulink url='&blfs-"
"book;postlfs/shadow.html'>the BLFS instructions</ulink> instead of this page "
"to build, rebuild, upgrade shadow."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:54
msgid ""
"If you would like to enforce the use of strong passwords, <ulink url='&blfs-"
"book;postlfs/linux-pam.html'>install and configure Linux-PAM</ulink> first.  "
"Then <ulink url='&blfs-book;postlfs/shadow.html'>install and configure "
"shadow with the PAM support</ulink>.  Finally <ulink url='&blfs-book;postlfs/"
"libpwquality.html'>install libpwquality and configure PAM to use it</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:63
msgid ""
"Disable the installation of the <command>groups</command> program and its "
"man pages, as Coreutils provides a better version. Also, prevent the "
"installation of manual pages that were already installed in <xref "
"linkend=\"ch-system-man-pages\"/>:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:68
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput remap=\"pre\">sed -i 's/groups$(EXEEXT) //' src/Makefile.in\n"
"find man -name Makefile.in -exec sed -i 's/groups\\.1 / /'   {} \\;\n"
"find man -name Makefile.in -exec sed -i 's/getspnam\\.3 / /' {} \\;\n"
"find man -name Makefile.in -exec sed -i 's/passwd\\.5 / /'   {} \\;</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:73
msgid ""
"Instead of using the default <emphasis>crypt</emphasis> method, use the much "
"more secure <emphasis>YESCRYPT</emphasis> method of password encryption, "
"which also allows passwords longer than 8 characters.  It is also necessary "
"to change the obsolete <filename class=\"directory\">/var/spool/mail</"
"filename> location for user mailboxes that Shadow uses by default to the "
"<filename class=\"directory\">/var/mail</filename> location used currently. "
"And, remove <filename class=\"directory\">/bin</filename> and <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/sbin</filename> from the <envar>PATH</envar>, since "
"they are simply symlinks to their counterparts in <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/usr</filename>."
msgstr ""

#.  known example: SPIRV-LLVM-Translator 
#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><warning><para>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:87
msgid ""
"Including <filename class=\"directory\">/bin</filename> and/or <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/sbin</filename> in the <envar>PATH</envar> variable may "
"cause some BLFS packages fail to build, so don't do that in the "
"<filename>.bashrc</filename> file or anywhere else."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:94
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput remap=\"pre\">sed -e 's:#ENCRYPT_METHOD DES:ENCRYPT_METHOD YESCRYPT:' \\\n"
"    -e 's:/var/spool/mail:/var/mail:'                   \\\n"
"    -e '/PATH=/{s@/sbin:@@;s@/bin:@@}'                  \\\n"
"    -i etc/login.defs</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:99
msgid "Prepare Shadow for compilation:"
msgstr "Prepare Shadow for compilation:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:101
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput remap=\"configure\">touch /usr/bin/passwd\n"
"./configure --sysconfdir=/etc   \\\n"
"            --disable-static    \\\n"
"            --with-{b,yes}crypt \\\n"
"            --without-libbsd    \\\n"
"            --disable-logind    \\\n"
"            --with-group-name-max-length=32</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><title>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:110
msgid "The meaning of the new configuration options:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:113
msgid "<command>touch /usr/bin/passwd</command>"
msgstr "<command>touch /usr/bin/passwd</command>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:115
msgid ""
"The file <filename>/usr/bin/passwd</filename> needs to exist because its "
"location is hardcoded in some programs; if it does not already exist, the "
"installation script will create it in the wrong place."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:123
msgid "<parameter>--with-{b,yes}crypt</parameter>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:125
msgid ""
"The shell expands this to two switches, <parameter>--with-bcrypt</parameter> "
"and <parameter>--with-yescrypt</parameter>.  They allow shadow to use the "
"Bcrypt and Yescrypt algorithms implemented by <application>Libxcrypt</"
"application> for hashing passwords.  These algorithms are more secure (in "
"particular, much more resistant to GPU-based attacks) than the traditional "
"SHA algorithms."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:137
msgid "<parameter>--with-group-name-max-length=32</parameter>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:139
msgid ""
"The longest permissible user name is 32 characters.  Make the maximum length "
"of a group name the same."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:145
msgid "<parameter>--disable-logind</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>--disable-logind</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:147
msgid ""
"This option makes Shadow (specifically, the <command>login</command> and "
"<command>who</command> programs) use the <filename>/run/utmp</filename> file "
"instead of logind to track the active login sessions, as logind isn't "
"available yet in the incomplete LFS system.  But as we've discussed in <xref "
"linkend='ch-tools-createfiles'/>, the <filename>/run/utmp</filename> file "
"format will be completely broken after year 2038.  The LFS editors will "
"attempt to resolve the issue before that year."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:180
msgid "<parameter>--without-libbsd</parameter>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:182
msgid ""
"Do not use the readpassphrase function from libbsd which is not in LFS.  Use "
"the internal copy instead."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:197
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput remap=\"install\">make exec_prefix=/usr install\n"
"make -C man install-man</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:203
msgid "Configuring Shadow"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><indexterm><secondary>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:207 en/chapter08/sysklogd.xml:70
#: en/chapter08/udev.xml:208 en/chapter09/clock.xml:15
#: en/chapter09/consoled.xml:15 en/chapter09/network.xml:15
#: en/chapter09/network.xml:146 en/chapter09/networkd.xml:15
#: en/chapter09/networkd.xml:283 en/chapter09/usage.xml:66
#: en/chapter09/usage.xml:265 en/chapter09/usage.xml:327
#: en/chapter09/usage.xml:596 en/chapter09/usage.xml:612
msgid "configuring"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:210
msgid ""
"This package contains utilities to add, modify, and delete users and groups; "
"set and change their passwords; and perform other administrative tasks. For "
"a full explanation of what <emphasis>password shadowing</emphasis> means, "
"see the <filename>doc/HOWTO</filename> file within the unpacked source tree. "
"If you use Shadow support, keep in mind that programs which need to verify "
"passwords (display managers, FTP programs, pop3 daemons, etc.)  must be "
"Shadow-compliant. That is, they must be able to work with shadowed passwords."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:219
msgid "To enable shadowed passwords, run the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:221
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>pwconv</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:223
msgid "To enable shadowed group passwords, run:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:225
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>grpconv</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:227
msgid ""
"Shadow's default configuration for the <command>useradd</command> utility "
"needs some explanation. First, the default action for the <command>useradd</"
"command> utility is to create the user and a group with the same name as the "
"user. By default the user ID (UID) and group ID (GID) numbers will begin at "
"1000. This means if you don't pass extra parameters to <command>useradd</"
"command>, each user will be a member of a unique group on the system. If "
"this behavior is undesirable, you'll need to pass either the <parameter>-g</"
"parameter> or <parameter>-N</parameter> parameter to <command>useradd</"
"command>, or else change the setting of <parameter>USERGROUPS_ENAB</"
"parameter> in <filename>/etc/login.defs</filename>. See <ulink role='man' "
"url='&man;useradd.8'>useradd(8)</ulink> for more information."
msgstr ""
"Shadow's default configuration for the <command>useradd</command> utility "
"needs some explanation. First, the default action for the <command>useradd</"
"command> utility is to create the user and a group with the same name as the "
"user. By default the user ID (UID) and group ID (GID) numbers will begin at "
"1000. This means if you don't pass extra parameters to <command>useradd</"
"command>, each user will be a member of a unique group on the system. If "
"this behavior is undesirable, you'll need to pass either the <parameter>-g</"
"parameter> or <parameter>-N</parameter> parameter to <command>useradd</"
"command>, or else change the setting of <parameter>USERGROUPS_ENAB</"
"parameter> in <filename>/etc/login.defs</filename>. See <ulink role='man' "
"url='&man;useradd.8'>useradd(8)</ulink> for more information."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:240
msgid ""
"Second, to change the default parameters, the file <filename>/etc/default/"
"useradd</filename> must be created and tailored to suit your particular "
"needs. Create it with:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:244
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>mkdir -p /etc/default\n"
"useradd -D --gid 999</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><title>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:248
msgid "<filename>/etc/default/useradd</filename> parameter explanations"
msgstr "<filename>/etc/default/useradd</filename> parameter explanations"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:251
msgid "<parameter>GROUP=999</parameter>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:253
msgid ""
"This parameter sets the beginning of the group numbers used in the "
"<filename>/etc/group</filename> file. The particular value 999 comes from "
"the <parameter>--gid</parameter> parameter above.  You may set it to any "
"desired value.  Note that <command>useradd</command> will never reuse a UID "
"or GID.  If the number identified in this parameter is used, it will use the "
"next available number. Note also that if you don't have a group with an ID "
"equal to this number on your system, then the first time you use "
"<command>useradd</command> without the <parameter>-g</parameter> parameter, "
"an error message will be generated&mdash;<computeroutput>useradd: unknown "
"GID 999</computeroutput>, even though the account has been created "
"correctly. That is why we created the group <systemitem "
"class=\"groupname\">users</systemitem> with this group ID in <xref "
"linkend='ch-tools-createfiles' role='.'/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:273
msgid "<parameter>CREATE_MAIL_SPOOL=yes</parameter>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:275
msgid ""
"This parameter causes <command>useradd</command> to create a mailbox file "
"for each new user. <command>useradd</command> will assign the group "
"ownership of this file to the <systemitem class=\"groupname\">mail</"
"systemitem> group with 0660 permissions. If you would rather not create "
"these files, issue the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><screen>
#: en/chapter08/shadow.xml:282
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>sed -i '/MAIL/s/yes/no/' /etc/default/useradd</userinput>"
msgstr ""

