"Gerard Beekmans\n"
"gerard@linuxfromscratch.org"
msgstr ""
"--\n"
"Gerard Beekmans\n"
"gerard@linuxfromscratch.org"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/prologue/organization.xml:11
msgid "Structure"
msgstr "구조"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/organization.xml:13
msgid "This book is divided into the following parts."
msgstr "이 책은 다음과 같은 부분으로 나뉩니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/prologue/organization.xml:16
msgid "Part I - Introduction"
msgstr "제1부 - 소개"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/prologue/organization.xml:18
msgid ""
"Part I explains a few important notes on how to proceed with the LFS "
"installation.  This section also provides meta-information about the book."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/prologue/organization.xml:24
msgid "Part II - Preparing for the Build"
msgstr "제2부 - 빌드 준비"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/prologue/organization.xml:26
msgid ""
"Part II describes how to prepare for the building process&mdash;making a "
"partition, downloading the packages, and compiling temporary tools."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/prologue/organization.xml:32
msgid "Part III - Building the LFS Cross Toolchain and Temporary Tools"
msgstr "제3부 - LFS 크로스 툴체인 및 임시 도구 빌드하기"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/prologue/organization.xml:34
msgid ""
"Part III provides instructions for building the tools needed for "
"constructing the final LFS system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/prologue/organization.xml:39
msgid "Part IV - Building the LFS System"
msgstr "제4부 - LFS 시스템 빌드"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/prologue/organization.xml:41
msgid ""
"Part IV guides the reader through the building of the LFS "
"system&mdash;compiling and installing all the packages one by one, setting "
"up the boot scripts, and installing the kernel. The resulting Linux system "
"is the foundation on which other software can be built to expand the system "
"as desired. At the end of this book, there is an easy to use reference "
"listing all of the programs, libraries, and important files that have been "
"installed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: en/prologue/organization.xml:51
msgid "Part V - Appendices"
msgstr "제5부 - 부록"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: en/prologue/organization.xml:53
msgid ""
"Part V provides information about the book itself including acronyms and "
"terms, acknowledgments, package dependencies, a listing of LFS boot scripts, "
"licenses for the distribution of the book, and a comprehensive index of "
"packages, programs, libraries, and scripts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <preface><title>
#: en/prologue/preface.xml:12
msgid "Preface"
msgstr "Preface"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/prologue/prerequisites.xml:11
msgid "Prerequisites"
msgstr "선행조건"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/prerequisites.xml:13
msgid ""
"Building an LFS system is not a simple task. It requires a certain level of "
"existing knowledge of Unix system administration in order to resolve "
"problems and correctly execute the commands listed. In particular, as an "
"absolute minimum, you should already know how to use the command line "
"(shell) to copy or move files and directories, list directory and file "
"contents, and change the current directory. It is also expected that you "
"know how to use and install Linux software."
msgstr ""
"LFS 시스템을 구축하는 것은 간단한 작업이 아닙니다. 문제를 해결하고 나열된 명"
"령어를 올바르게 실행하기 위해서는 유닉스 시스템 관리와 관련된 어느 정도의 지"
"식이 필요합니다. 특히, 최소한의 요구 사항으로서 셸(shell) 명령행을 사용하여 "
"파일과 디렉터리를 복사하거나 이동하고, 디렉터리와 파일의 내용을 나열하며, 현"
"재 디렉터리를 변경하는 방법 등을 이미 알고 있어야 합니다. 또한 리눅스 소프트"
"웨어를 사용하고 설치하는 방법도 알고 있어야 합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/prerequisites.xml:22
msgid ""
"Because the LFS book assumes <emphasis>at least</emphasis> this basic level "
"of skill, the various LFS support forums are unlikely to provide you with "
"much assistance in these areas. You will find that your questions regarding "
"such basic knowledge will likely go unanswered (or you will simply be "
"referred to the LFS essential pre-reading list)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/prerequisites.xml:28
msgid "Before building an LFS system, we urge you to read these articles:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/prerequisites.xml:32
msgid ""
"Software-Building-HOWTO <ulink url=\"https://tldp.org/HOWTO/Software-"
"Building-HOWTO.html\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/prerequisites.xml:35
msgid ""
"This is a comprehensive guide to building and installing <quote>generic</"
"quote> Unix software packages under Linux. Although it was written some time "
"ago, it still provides a good summary of the basic techniques used to build "
"and install software."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/prerequisites.xml:42
msgid ""
"Beginner's Guide to Installing from Source <ulink url=\"https://"
"moi.vonos.net/linux/beginners-installing-from-source/\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/prerequisites.xml:45
msgid ""
"This guide provides a good summary of the basic skills and techniques needed "
"to build software from source code."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/prologue/standards.xml:11
msgid "LFS and Standards"
msgstr "LFS 및 표준"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/standards.xml:16
msgid ""
"The structure of LFS follows Linux standards as closely as possible.  The "
"primary standards are:"
msgstr "LFS의 구조는 가능한 한 리눅스 표준을 밀접하게 따릅니다. 주요 표준:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/standards.xml:21
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"https://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/9699919799/\"> "
"POSIX.1-2008</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/standards.xml:25
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"https://refspecs.linuxfoundation.org/FHS_3.0/fhs/index.html\"> "
"Filesystem Hierarchy Standard (FHS) Version 3.0</ulink>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/standards.xml:31
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"https://refspecs.linuxfoundation.org/lsb.shtml\">Linux Standard "
"Base (LSB) Version 5.0 (2015)</ulink>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/standards.xml:34
msgid ""
"The LSB has four separate specifications: Core, Desktop, Languages, and "
"Imaging.  Some parts of Core and Desktop specifications are architecture "
"specific.  There are also two trial specifications: Gtk3 and Graphics.  LFS "
"attempts to conform to the LSB specifications for the IA32 (32-bit x86) or "
"AMD64 (x86_64)  architectures discussed in the previous section."
msgstr ""
"LSB에는 독립된 4개 규격이 있습니다: 핵심(Core), 데스크톱(Desktop), 언어"
"(Languages), 이미지(Imaging). 핵심 및 데스크톱 규격의 일부 항목은 아키텍처에 "
"따라 달라지기도 합니다. 또한 Gtk3와 그래픽(Graphics)이라는 두 가지 시험용 규"
"격도 존재합니다. LFS는 이전 섹션에서 다룬 IA32(32비트 x86) 또는 "
"AMD64(x86_64) 아키텍처에 대하여 LSB 규격을 준수하고자 노력합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><note><para>
#: en/prologue/standards.xml:41
msgid ""
"Many people do not agree with these requirements.  The main purpose of the "
"LSB is to ensure that proprietary software can be installed and run on a "
"compliant system.  Since LFS is source based, the user has complete control "
"over what packages are desired; you may choose not to install some packages "
"that are specified by the LSB."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/standards.xml:51
msgid ""
"While it is possible to create a complete system that will pass the LSB "
"certification tests <quote>from scratch,</quote> this can't be done without "
"many additional packages that are beyond the scope of the LFS book.  "
"Installation instructions for some of these additional packages can be found "
"in BLFS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><bridgehead>
#: en/prologue/standards.xml:57
msgid "Packages supplied by LFS needed to satisfy the LSB Requirements"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/prologue/standards.xml:63 en/prologue/standards.xml:111
#: en/prologue/standards.xml:160
msgid "<emphasis>LSB Core:</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis>LSB Core:</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/standards.xml:66
msgid ""
"Bash, Bc, Binutils, Coreutils, Diffutils, File, Findutils, Gawk, GCC, "
"Gettext, Glibc, Grep, Gzip, M4, Man-DB, Procps, Psmisc, Sed, Shadow, <phrase "
"revision='sysv'>SysVinit</phrase><phrase revision='systemd'>Systemd</"
"phrase>, Tar, Util-linux, Zlib"
msgstr ""
"Bash, Bc, Binutils, Coreutils, Diffutils, File, Findutils, Gawk, GCC, "
"Gettext, Glibc, Grep, Gzip, M4, Man-DB, Procps, Psmisc, Sed, Shadow, <phrase "
"revision='sysv'>SysVinit</phrase><phrase revision='systemd'>Systemd</"
