#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/prologue/typography.xml:11
msgid "Typography"
msgstr "타이포그래피"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/typography.xml:13
msgid ""
"To make things easier to follow, there are a few typographical conventions "
"used throughout this book. This section contains some examples of the "
"typographical format found throughout Linux From Scratch."
msgstr ""
"내용을 더 쉽게 따라갈 수 있도록 이 책 전반에서 몇 가지 타이포그래피 관례를 사"
"용합니다. 이 섹션에는 Linux From Scratch 전반에서 볼 수 있는 타이포그래피 형"
"식의 몇 가지 예시가 들어 있습니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/prologue/typography.xml:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>./configure --prefix=/usr</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/typography.xml:20
msgid ""
"This form of text is designed to be typed exactly as seen unless otherwise "
"noted in the surrounding text. It is also used in the explanation sections "
"to identify which of the commands is being referenced."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/typography.xml:24
msgid ""
"In some cases, a logical line is extended to two or more physical lines with "
"a backslash at the end of the line."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/prologue/typography.xml:27
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>CC=\"gcc -B/usr/bin/\" ../binutils-2.18/configure \\\n"
"  --prefix=/tools --disable-nls --disable-werror</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/typography.xml:30
msgid ""
"Note that the backslash must be followed by an immediate return.  Other "
"whitespace characters like spaces or tab characters will create incorrect "
"results."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/prologue/typography.xml:34
#, no-wrap
msgid "<computeroutput>install-info: unknown option '--dir-file=/mnt/lfs/usr/info/dir'</computeroutput>"
msgstr "<computeroutput>install-info: unknown option '--dir-file=/mnt/lfs/usr/info/dir'</computeroutput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/typography.xml:36
msgid ""
"This form of text (fixed-width text) shows screen output, usually as the "
"result of commands issued.  If you are reading the book in the HTML format "
"(instead of PDF), the text should be blue."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/typography.xml:40
msgid ""
"The fixed-width text is also used to show filenames, such as <filename>/etc/"
"ld.so.conf</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><note><para>
#: en/prologue/typography.xml:44
msgid ""
"Please configure your browser to display fixed-width text with a good "
"monospaced font, with which you can distinguish the glyphs of <literal>Il1</"
"literal> or <literal>O0</literal> clearly."
msgstr ""
"브라우저가 고정 폭(fixed-width) 텍스트를 표시할 때 좋은 고정 폭 글꼴"
"(monospaced font)을 사용하도록 설정하십시오. 특히 <literal>Il1</literal>(대문"
"자 i, 소문자 l, 숫자 1)이나 <literal>O0</literal>(대문자 O, 숫자 0)의 글자 모"
"양(glyph)을 명확하게 구별할 수 있는 글꼴이어야 합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/typography.xml:49
msgid "<emphasis>Emphasis</emphasis>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/typography.xml:51
msgid ""
"This form of text is used for several purposes in the book. Its main purpose "
"is to emphasize important points or items."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/typography.xml:54
msgid "<ulink url=\"&lfs-root;\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/typography.xml:56
msgid ""
"This format is used for hyperlinks both within the LFS community and to "
"external pages. It includes HOWTOs, download locations, and websites."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: en/prologue/typography.xml:59
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; $LFS/etc/group &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal>root:x:0:\n"
"bin:x:1:\n"
"......</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/typography.xml:65
msgid ""
"This format is used when creating configuration files. The first command "
"tells the system to create the file <filename>$LFS/etc/group</filename> from "
"whatever is typed on the following lines until the sequence End Of File "
"(EOF)  is encountered. Therefore, this entire section is generally typed as "
"seen."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/typography.xml:71
msgid "<replaceable>&lt;REPLACED TEXT&gt;</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/typography.xml:73
msgid ""
"This format is used to encapsulate text that is not to be typed as seen or "
"for copy-and-paste operations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/typography.xml:76
msgid "<replaceable>[OPTIONAL TEXT]</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/typography.xml:78
msgid "This format is used to encapsulate text that is optional."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/typography.xml:80
msgid "<ulink role='man' url='&man;passwd.5'>passwd(5)</ulink>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/typography.xml:82
msgid ""
"This format is used to refer to a specific manual (man) page. The number "
"inside parentheses indicates a specific section inside the manuals. For "
"example, <command>passwd</command> has two man pages. Per LFS installation "
"instructions, those two man pages will be located at <filename>/usr/share/"
"man/man1/passwd.1</filename> and <filename>/usr/share/man/man5/passwd.5</"
"filename>. When the book uses <ulink role='man' url='&man;/"
"passwd.5'>passwd(5)</ulink> it is specifically referring to <filename>/usr/"
"share/man/man5/passwd.5</filename>.  <command>man passwd</command> will "
"print the first man page it finds that matches <quote>passwd,</quote> which "
"will be <filename>/usr/share/man/man1/passwd.1</filename>. For this example, "
"you will need to run <command>man 5 passwd</command> in order to read the "
"page being specified. Note that most man pages do not have duplicate page "
"names in different sections. Therefore, <command>man "
"<replaceable>&lt;program name&gt;</replaceable></command> is generally "
"sufficient.  In the LFS book these references to man pages are also "
"hyperlinks, so clicking on such a reference will open the man page rendered "
"in HTML from <ulink url='https://man.archlinux.org/'>Arch Linux manual "
"pages</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:11
msgid "Rationale for Packages in the Book"
msgstr "이 책 안의 패키지 선정 근거"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:13
msgid ""
"The goal of LFS is to build a complete and usable foundation-level "
"system&mdash;including all the packages needed to replicate itself&mdash;and "
"providing a relatively minimal base from which to customize a more complete "
"system based on the user's choices.  This does not mean that LFS is the "
"smallest system possible.  Several important packages are included that are "
"not, strictly speaking, required.  The list below documents the reasons each "
"package in the book has been included."
msgstr ""
"LFS의 목표는 스스로를 복제하는 데 필요한 모든 패키지를 포함하여, 완전하고 사"
"용 가능한 기초 수준의 시스템을 구축하는 것입니다. 또한 사용자의 선택에 따라 "
"더 완전한 시스템을 맞춤 설정할 수 있도록 상대적으로 최소한의 기반을 제공합니"
"다. 이것이 LFS가 가능한 가장 작은 시스템이라는 의미는 아닙니다. 엄밀히 말해 "
"필수적이지는 않지만 중요한 몇 가지 패키지들이 포함되어 있습니다. 아래 목록은 "
"이 책에 포함된 각 패키지의 선정 이유를 설명합니다."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:26
msgid ""
"This package contains utilities to administer Access Control Lists, which "
"are used to define fine-grained discretionary access rights for files and "
"directories."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:35
msgid ""
"This package contains programs for managing extended attributes on file "
"system objects."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:43
msgid ""
"This package supplies programs for producing shell scripts that can "
"automatically configure source code from a developer's template. It is often "
"needed to rebuild a package after the build procedure has been updated."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:52
msgid ""
"This package contains programs for generating Make files from a template. It "
"is often needed to rebuild a package after the build procedure has been "
"updated."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:60
msgid ""
"This package satisfies an LSB core requirement to provide a Bourne Shell "
"interface to the system.  It was chosen over other shell packages because of "
"its common usage and extensive capabilities."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:69
msgid ""
"This package provides an arbitrary precision numeric processing language.  "
"It satisfies a requirement for building the Linux kernel."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:76
msgid ""
"This package supplies a linker, an assembler, and other tools for handling "
"object files. The programs in this package are needed to compile most of the "
"packages in an LFS system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:84
msgid ""
"This package contains the GNU version of yacc (Yet Another Compiler "
"Compiler) needed to build several of the LFS programs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:91
msgid ""
"This package contains programs for compressing and decompressing files.  It "
"is required to decompress many LFS packages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:104
msgid ""
"This package contains a number of essential programs for viewing and "
"manipulating files and directories. These programs are needed for command "
"line file management, and are necessary for the installation procedures of "
"every package in LFS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:113
msgid ""
"This package contains programs to implement a message bus system, a simple "
"way for applications to talk to one another."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:121
msgid "This package supplies a framework for testing other programs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:127
msgid ""
"This package contains programs that show the differences between files or "
"directories. These programs can be used to create patches, and are also used "
"in many packages' build procedures."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:135
msgid ""
"This package supplies utilities for handling the ext2, ext3 and ext4 file "
"systems.  These are the most common and thoroughly tested file systems that "
"Linux supports."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:143
msgid ""
"This package yields a relatively small XML parsing library.  It is required "
"by the XML::Parser Perl module."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:150
msgid ""
"This package contains a program for carrying out scripted dialogues with "
"other interactive programs.  It is commonly used for testing other packages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:158
msgid ""
"This package contains a utility for determining the type of a given file or "
"files. A few packages need it in their build scripts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:165
msgid ""
"This package provides programs to find files in a file system.  It is used "
"in many packages' build scripts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:172
msgid ""
"This package contains a utility for generating programs that recognize "
"patterns in text.  It is the GNU version of the lex (lexical analyzer) "
"program.  It is required to build several LFS packages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:181
msgid ""
"This package supplies programs for manipulating text files.  It is the GNU "
"version of awk (Aho-Weinberg-Kernighan). It is used in many other packages' "
"build scripts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:189
msgid ""
"This is the Gnu Compiler Collection.  It contains the C and C++ compilers as "
"well as several others not built by LFS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:197
msgid ""
"This package contains the GNU Database Manager library.  It is used by one "
"other LFS package, Man-DB."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:204
msgid ""
"This package provides utilities and libraries for the internationalization "
"and localization of many packages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:211
msgid ""
"This package contains the main C library.  Linux programs will not run "
"without it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:218
msgid ""
"This package supplies math libraries that provide useful functions for "
"arbitrary precision arithmetic.  It is needed to build GCC."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:225
msgid ""
"This package produces a program that generates a perfect hash function from "
"a set of keys. It is required by <phrase revision='sysv'>Udev</phrase> "
"<phrase revision='systemd'>Systemd</phrase>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:234
msgid ""
"This package contains programs for searching through files. These programs "
"are used by most packages' build scripts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:241
msgid ""
"This package contributes programs for processing and formatting text.  One "
"important function of these programs is to format man pages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:248
msgid ""
"This is the Grand Unified Boot Loader.  It is the most flexible of several "
"boot loaders available."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:256
msgid ""
"This package contains programs for compressing and decompressing files. It "
"is needed to decompress many packages in LFS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:262
msgid "Iana-etc"
msgstr "Iana-etc"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:264
msgid ""
"This package provides data for network services and protocols.  It is needed "
"to enable proper networking capabilities."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:271
msgid "This package supplies programs for basic network administration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:278
msgid ""
"This package contributes tools for extracting translatable strings from "
"source files."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <appendix><bridgehead>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:283 en/appendices/dependencies.xml:1414
msgid "IProute2"
msgstr "IProute2"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:285
msgid ""
"This package contains programs for basic and advanced IPv4 and IPv6 "
"networking.  It was chosen over the other common network tools package (net-"
"tools) for its IPv6 capabilities."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:293
msgid ""
"This package is a Python module for text templating.  It's required to build "
"Systemd."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:300
msgid ""
"This package produces key-table files, keyboard utilities for non-US "
"keyboards, and a number of console fonts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:307
msgid ""
"This package supplies programs needed to administer Linux kernel modules."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:314
msgid ""
"This package contains a very nice text file viewer that allows scrolling up "
"or down when viewing a file.  Many packages use it for paging the output."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:322
msgid ""
"This package implements the userspace interfaces to the POSIX 1003.1e "
"capabilities available in Linux kernels."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:330
msgid ""
"The elfutils project provides libraries and tools for ELF files and DWARF "
"data.  Most utilities in this package are available in other packages, but "
"the library is needed to build the Linux kernel using the default (and most "
"efficient) configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <appendix><bridgehead>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:338 en/appendices/dependencies.xml:1700
msgid "Libffi"
msgstr "Libffi"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:340
msgid ""
"This package implements a portable, high level programming interface to "
"various calling conventions.  Some programs may not know at the time of "
"compilation what arguments are to be passed to a function. For instance, an "
"interpreter may be told at run-time about the number and types of arguments "
"used to call a given function. Libffi can be used in such programs to "
"provide a bridge from the interpreter program to compiled code."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:353
msgid ""
"The Libpipeline package supplies a library for manipulating pipelines of "
"subprocesses in a flexible and convenient way. It is required by the Man-DB "
"package."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:361
msgid ""
"This package contains the GNU generic library support script. It wraps the "
"complexity of using shared libraries into a consistent, portable interface.  "
"It is needed by the test suites in other LFS packages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:370
msgid ""
"This package provides the <systemitem class='library'>libcrypt</systemitem> "
"library needed by various packages (notably, Shadow) for hashing passwords.  "
"It replaces the obsolete <systemitem class='library'>libcrypt</systemitem> "
"implementation in Glibc."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:379
msgid "Linux Kernel"
msgstr "Linux Kernel"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:381
msgid ""
"This package is the Operating System.  It is the Linux in the GNU/Linux "
"environment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:388
msgid ""
"This package provides a general text macro processor useful as a build tool "
"for other programs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:395
msgid ""
"This package contains a program for directing the building of packages.  It "
"is required by almost every package in LFS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:402
msgid ""
"This package is a Python module for processing strings in HTML/XHTML/XML "
"safely.  Jinja2 requires this package."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:409
msgid ""
"This package contains programs for finding and viewing man pages.  It was "
"chosen instead of the <application>man</application> package because of its "
"superior internationalization capabilities.  It supplies the man program."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:418
msgid "This package provides the actual contents of the basic Linux man pages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:425
msgid ""
"This package provides a software tool for automating the building of "
"software. The main goal of Meson is to minimize the amount of time that "
"software developers need to spend configuring a build system.  It's required "
"to build Systemd, as well as many BLFS packages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:436
msgid ""
"This package supplies arithmetic functions for complex numbers. It is "
"required by GCC."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:443
msgid ""
"This package contains functions for multiple precision arithmetic.  It is "
"required by GCC."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:450
msgid ""
"This package furnishes a small build system with a focus on speed.  It is "
"designed to have its input files generated by a higher-level build system, "
"and to run builds as fast as possible.  This package is required by Meson."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:460
msgid ""
"This package contains libraries for terminal-independent handling of "
"character screens.  It is often used to provide cursor control for a menuing "
"system. It is needed by a number of the packages in LFS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:467
msgid "Openssl"
msgstr "Openssl"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:469
msgid ""
"This package provides management tools and libraries relating to "
"cryptography. These supply cryptographic functions to other packages, "
"including the Linux kernel."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:477
msgid ""
"This package contains a program for modifying or creating files by applying "
"a <emphasis>patch</emphasis> file typically created by the "
"<application>diff</application> program.  It is needed by the build "
"procedure for several LFS packages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:486
msgid ""
"This package provides a set of functions that implement regular expression "
"pattern matching using the same syntax and semantics as Perl 5."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:494
msgid ""
"This package is an interpreter for the runtime language PERL. It is needed "
"for the installation and test suites of several LFS packages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:502
msgid ""
"This package contains a program which helps to configure compiler and linker "
"flags for development libraries.  The program can be used as a drop-in "
"replacement of <command>pkg-config</command>, which is needed by the "
"building system of many packages.  It's maintained more actively and "
"slightly faster than the original Pkg-config package."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:511
msgid "Procps-NG"
msgstr "Procps-NG"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:513
msgid ""
"This package contains programs for monitoring processes. These programs are "
"useful for system administration, and are also used by the LFS Bootscripts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:521
msgid ""
"This package produces programs for displaying information about running "
"processes. These programs are useful for system administration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:527
msgid "Python 3"
msgstr "Python 3"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:529
msgid ""
"This package provides an interpreted language that has a design philosophy "
"emphasizing code readability."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:537
msgid ""
"This package is a set of libraries that offer command-line editing and "
"history capabilities.  It is used by Bash."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:544
msgid ""
"This package allows editing of text without opening it in a text editor. It "
"is also needed by many LFS packages' configure scripts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:552
msgid "This package contains programs for handling passwords securely."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:559
msgid ""
"This package provides a serverless, zero-configuration, transactional SQL "
"database engine."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:566
msgid ""
"This package supplies programs for logging system messages, such as those "
"emitted by the kernel or daemon processes when unusual events occur."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <appendix><bridgehead>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:572 en/appendices/dependencies.xml:2992
msgid "Systemd"
msgstr "Systemd"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:574
msgid ""
"This package provides an <application>init</application> program and several "
"additional boot and system control capabilities as an alternative to "
"SysVinit.  It is used by many Linux distributions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:583
msgid ""
"This package provides the <application>init</application> program, the "
"parent of all the other processes on a running Linux system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:591
msgid ""
"This package is a device manager.  It dynamically controls the ownership, "
"permissions, names, and symbolic links of device nodes in the /dev directory "
"when devices are added to or removed from the system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:600
msgid ""
"This package provides archiving and extraction capabilities of virtually all "
"the packages used in LFS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:607
msgid ""
"This package contains the Tool Command Language used in many test suites."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:614
msgid ""
"This package supplies programs for reading, writing, and converting info "
"pages.  It is used in the installation procedures of many LFS packages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:622
msgid ""
"This package contains miscellaneous utility programs.  Among them are "
"utilities for handling file systems, consoles, partitions, and messages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:630
msgid ""
"This package provides an editor. It was chosen because of its compatibility "
"with the classic vi editor and its huge number of powerful capabilities.  An "
"editor is a very personal choice for many users. Any other editor can be "
"substituted, if you wish."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <appendix><bridgehead>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:637 en/appendices/dependencies.xml:2443
#: en/appendices/dependencies.xml:3386
msgid "Wheel"
msgstr "Wheel"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:639
msgid ""
"This package supplies a Python module that is the reference implementation "
"of the Python wheel packaging standard."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:647
msgid "This package is a Perl module that interfaces with Expat."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:651
msgid "XZ Utils"
msgstr "XZ Utils"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:653
msgid ""
"This package contains programs for compressing and decompressing files.  It "
"provides the highest compression generally available and is useful for "
"decompressing packages in XZ or LZMA format."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:661
msgid ""
"This package contains compression and decompression routines used by some "
"programs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <appendix><bridgehead>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:666 en/appendices/dependencies.xml:3544
msgid "Zstd"
msgstr "Zstd"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/prologue/why.xml:668
msgid ""
"This package supplies compression and decompression routines used by some "
"programs. It provides high compression ratios and a very wide range of "
"compression / speed trade-offs."
msgstr ""

